nBeef and Oyster pie
cBeef
d52878
iSeason the beef cubes with salt and black pepper.
iHeat a tablespoon of oil in the frying pan and fry the meat over a high heat.
iDo this in three batches so that you don’t overcrowd the pan, transferring the meat to a large flameproof casserole dish once it is browned all over.
iAdd extra oil if the pan seems dry.
iIn the same pan, add another tablespoon of oil and cook the shallots for 4-5 minutes, then add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds.
iAdd the bacon and fry until slightly browned.
iTransfer the onion and bacon mixture to the casserole dish and add the herbs.
iPreheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.
iPour the stout into the frying pan and bring to the boil, stirring to lift any stuck-on browned bits from the bottom of the pan.
iPour the stout over the beef in the casserole dish and add the stock.
iCover the casserole and place it in the oven for 1½-2 hours, or until the beef is tender and the sauce is reduced.
iSkim off any surface fat, taste and add salt and pepper if necessary, then stir in the cornflour paste.
iPut the casserole dish on the hob – don’t forget that it will be hot – and simmer for 1-2 minutes, stirring, until thickened.
iLeave to cool.
iIncrease the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.
iTo make the pastry, put the flour and salt in a very large bowl.
iGrate the butter and stir it into the flour in three batches.
iGradually add 325ml/11fl oz cold water – you may not need it all – and stir with a round-bladed knife until the mixture just comes together.
iKnead the pastry lightly into a ball on a lightly floured surface and set aside 250g/9oz for the pie lid.
iRoll the rest of the pastry out until about 2cm/¾in larger than the dish you’re using.
iLine the dish with the pastry then pile in the filling, tucking the oysters in as well.
iBrush the edge of the pastry with beaten egg.
iRoll the remaining pastry until slightly larger than your dish and gently lift over the filling, pressing the edges firmly to seal, then trim with a sharp knife.
iBrush with beaten egg to glaze.
iPut the dish on a baking tray and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the pastry is golden-brown and the filling is bubbling.
