nBeef Banh Mi Bowls with Sriracha Mayo, Carrot & Pickled Cucumber
cBeef
d52997
iPlace rice in a fine-mesh sieve and rinse until water runs clear.
iAdd to a small pot with 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings) and a pinch of salt.
iBring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.
iCook until rice is tender, 15 minutes.
iKeep covered off heat for at least 10 minutes or until ready to serve.
iMeanwhile, wash and dry all produce.
iPeel and finely chop garlic.
iZest and quarter lime (for 4 servings, zest 1 lime and quarter both).
iTrim and halve cucumber lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons.
iHalve, peel, and medium dice onion.
iTrim, peel, and grate carrot.
iIn a medium bowl, combine cucumber, juice from half the lime, ¼ tsp sugar (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt.
iIn a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, a pinch of garlic, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much sriracha as you’d like.
iSeason with salt and pepper.
iHeat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
iAdd onion and cook, stirring, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
iAdd beef, remaining garlic, and 2 tsp sugar (4 tsp for 4 servings).
iCook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is browned and cooked through, 4-5 minutes.
iStir in soy sauce.
iTurn off heat; taste and season with salt and pepper.
iFluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest and 1 TBSP butter.
iDivide rice between bowls.
iArrange beef, grated carrot, and pickled cucumber on top.
iTop with a squeeze of lime juice.
iDrizzle with sriracha mayo.
