nBeef Dumpling Stew
cBeef
d52873
iPreheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.
iFor the beef stew, heat the oil and butter in an ovenproof casserole and fry the beef until browned on all sides.
iSprinkle over the flour and cook for a further 2-3 minutes.
iAdd the garlic and all the vegetables and fry for 1-2 minutes.
iStir in the wine, stock and herbs, then add the Worcestershire sauce and balsamic vinegar, to taste.
iSeason with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
iCover with a lid, transfer to the oven and cook for about two hours, or until the meat is tender.
iFor the dumplings, sift the flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
iAdd the suet and enough water to form a thick dough.
iWith floured hands, roll spoonfuls of the dough into small balls.
iAfter two hours, remove the lid from the stew and place the balls on top of the stew.
iCover, return to the oven and cook for a further 20 minutes, or until the dumplings have swollen and are tender.
i(If you prefer your dumplings with a golden top, leave the lid off when returning to the oven.
iTo serve, place a spoonful of mashed potato onto each of four serving plates and top with the stew and dumplings.
iSprinkle with chopped parsley.
