nBeef stroganoff
cBeef
d52834
iHeat the olive oil in a non-stick frying pan then add the sliced onion and cook on a medium heat until completely softened, so around 15 mins, adding a little splash of water if they start to stick at all.
iCrush in the garlic and cook for a 2-3 mins further, then add the butter.
iOnce the butter is foaming a little, add the mushrooms and cook for around 5 mins until completely softened.
iSeason everything well, then tip onto a plate.
iTip the flour into a bowl with a big pinch of salt and pepper, then toss the steak in the seasoned flour.
iAdd the steak pieces to the pan, splashing in a little oil if the pan looks particularly dry, and fry for 3-4 mins, until well coloured.
iTip the onions and mushrooms back into the pan.
iWhisk the crème fraîche, mustard and beef stock together, then pour into the pan.
iCook over a medium heat for around 5 mins.
iScatter with parsley, then serve with pappardelle or rice.
