nBeef Sunday Roast
cBeef
d52824
iCook the Broccoli and Carrots in a pan of boiling water until tender.
iRoast the Beef and Potatoes in the oven for 45mins, the potatoes may need to be checked regularly to not overcook.
iHeat oven to 230C/fan 210C/gas 8.
iTo make the batter, tip 140g plain flour into a bowl and beat in four eggs until smooth.
iGradually add 200ml milk and carry on beating until the mix is completely lump-free.
iSeason with salt and pepper.
iPour the batter into a jug, then remove the hot tins from the oven.
iCarefully and evenly pour the batter into the holes.
iPlace the tins back in the oven and leave undisturbed for 20-25 mins until the puddings have puffed up and browned.
iServe immediately.
iPlate up and add the Gravy as desired.
