nBitterballen (Dutch meatballs)
cBeef
d52979
iMelt the butter in a skillet or pan.
iWhen melted, add the flour little by little and stir into a thick paste.
iSlowly stir in the stock, making sure the roux absorbs the liquid.
iSimmer for a couple of minutes on a low heat while you stir in the onion, parsley and the shredded meat.
iThe mixture should thicken and turn into a heavy, thick sauce.
iPour the mixture into a shallow container, cover and refrigerate for several hours, or until the sauce has solidified.
iTake a heaping tablespoon of the cold, thick sauce and quickly roll it into a small ball.
iRoll lightly through the flour, then the egg and finally the breadcrumbs.
iMake sure that the egg covers the whole surface of the bitterbal.
iWhen done, refrigerate the snacks while the oil in your fryer heats up to 190C (375F).
iFry four bitterballen at a time, until golden.
iServe on a plate with a nice grainy or spicy mustard.
