nEgyptian Fatteh
cBeef
d53031
iTo prepare bread for bottom of dish: Take pita bread and rip into bite size pieces.
iIn a frying pan, add about a 1/4 stick of butter, add bread pieces and fry until golden brown and crisp.
iPut these pieces in a glass baking dish, preferably a square sized dish.
iSet aside.
iThen add to same pan, a little more butter, salt, approximately 2 cloves of crushed fresh garlic, and a teaspoon or so of cumin stir around a bit until you can smell aroma, then add fried bread pieces to this mixture, stir to coat bread and put back into glass baking dish.
iSet aside.
iTo prepare meat: put some butter in a pot, stir fry meat until brown, add 1 onion quartered, salt & pepper, 1 cube of chicken bouillon and water to cover meat.
iBring to a boil, turn down to simmer, cover and cook until tender, approximately 2 hours.
iAfter meat has cooled, take out chunks of meat and put in a bowl, set aside.
iReserve soup from the meat separately.
iTo prepare the rice: Put some butter into a pot, add shareya (fideo noodles) like a handful or so, keep stirring until golden brown, not too dark, but very golden.
iThen add two cups of rice, stir a little bit until some of the rice turns an opaque white.
iAdd 2-1/4 cups of water and salt to taste.
iBring to a boil, cover and turn down to simmer, cook until tender.
iTest the rice tenderness after about 35 minutes.
iNow take some of the soup from meat and add to the top of the bread pieces in baking dish to saturate.
iAdd cooked rice on top of bread pieces.
iSlowly spoon remainder of soup onto rice, looking at glass dish sides to see level of soup, should reach just to top of rice, don’t worry, this doesn’t have to be exact.
iNow you’re ready to make the sauce and fry the meat to put on top.
iTo prepare red sauce: In a pan, add a little oil or butter, crushed tomato, a half teaspoon of tomato paste, salt & pepper, 2 cloves of fresh crushed garlic and cumin.
iAdd also approximately 3 tablespoons of vinegar, stir this until you smell aroma and it is a bit smooth.
iIt should be a bit thick, not watery, but if too thick you can add a bit of water.
iSpread with a wooden spoon atop the rice to cover.
iTo fry meat: In a pan add a bit of butter or oil, the meat, just a touch of tomato paste, about a tablespoon of fresh crushed garlic, salt & pepper, a teaspoon of cumin.
iCook until meat is golden fried.
iSpoon this atop the rice and serve.
