nGołąbki (cabbage roll)
cBeef
d53021
iBring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
iPlace cabbage head into water, cover pot, and cook until cabbage leaves are slightly softened enough to remove from head, 3 minutes.
iRemove cabbage from pot and let cabbage sit until leaves are cool enough to handle, about 10 minutes.
iRemove 18 whole leaves from the cabbage head, cutting out any thick tough center ribs.
iSet whole leaves aside.
iChop the remainder of the cabbage head and spread it in the bottom of a casserole dish.
iMelt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
iCook and stir onion in hot butter until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
iCool.
iStir onion, beef, pork, rice, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper together in a large bowl.
iPreheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
iPlace about 1/2 cup beef mixture on a cabbage leaf.
iRoll cabbage around beef mixture, tucking in sides to create an envelope around the meat.
iRepeat with remaining leaves and meat mixture.
iPlace cabbage rolls in a layer atop the chopped cabbage in the casserole dish; season rolls with salt and black pepper.
iWhisk tomato soup, tomato juice, and ketchup together in a bowl.
iPour tomato soup mixture over cabbage rolls and cover dish wish aluminum foil.
iBake in the preheated oven until cabbage is tender and meat is cooked through, about 1 hour.
