nIrish stew
cBeef
d52781
iHeat the oven to 180C/350F/gas mark 4.
iDrain and rinse the soaked wheat, put it in a medium pan with lots of water, bring to a boil and simmer for an hour, until cooked.
iDrain and set aside.
iSeason the lamb with a teaspoon of salt and some black pepper.
iPut one tablespoon of oil in a large, deep sauté pan for which you have a lid; place on a medium-high heat.
iAdd some of the lamb – don't overcrowd the pan – and sear for four minutes on all sides.
iTransfer to a bowl, and repeat with the remaining lamb, adding oil as needed.
iLower the heat to medium and add a tablespoon of oil to the pan.
iAdd the shallots and fry for four minutes, until caramelised.
iTip these into the lamb bowl, and repeat with the remaining vegetables until they are all nice and brown, adding more oil as you need it.
iOnce all the vegetables are seared and removed from the pan, add the wine along with the sugar, herbs, a teaspoon of salt and a good grind of black pepper.
iBoil on a high heat for about three minutes.
iTip the lamb, vegetables and whole wheat back into the pot, and add the stock.
iCover and boil for five minutes, then transfer to the oven for an hour and a half.
iRemove the stew from the oven and check the liquid; if there is a lot, remove the lid and boil for a few minutes.
