nSoy-Glazed Meatloaves with Wasabi Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Carrots
cBeef
d52992
i1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
iWash and dry all produce.
iDice potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
iTrim, peel, and cut carrots on a diagonal into 1/2-inch-thick pieces.
iTrim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens; finely chop whites.
iPeel and finely chop garlic.
i2. In a medium bowl, soak bread with 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings); break up with your hands until pasty.
iStir in beef, sriracha, scallion whites, half the garlic, salt (we used 3/4 tsp kosher salt; 11/2 tsp for 4), and pepper.
iForm into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).
iPlace on one side of a baking sheet.
iToss carrots on empty side of same sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
i(For 4, spread meatloaves out across whole sheet and add carrots to a second sheet.
i) Bake for 20 minutes (we'll glaze the meatloaves then).
i3. Meanwhile, place potatoes in a medium pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
itender, 12-15 minutes.
iReserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.
iWhile potatoes cook, in a small bowl, combine soy sauce, garlic powder, 1/4 cup ketchup (1/2 cup for 4 servings), and 2 tsp sugar (4 tsp for 4).
i4. Once meatloaves and carrots have baked 20 minutes, remove from oven.
ithe rest for serving); return to oven until carrots are browned and tender, meatloaves are cooked through, and glaze is tacky, 4-5 minutes more.
i5. Meanwhile, melt 2 TBSP butter (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in pot used for potatoes over medium heat.
iuntil fragrant, 30 seconds.
iAdd potatoes and 1/4 tsp wasabi.
iMash, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as necessary until smooth.
iSeason with salt and pepper.
i6. Divide meatloaves, mashed potatoes, and roasted carrots between plates.
iSprinkle with scallion greens and serve with remaining ketchup glaze on the side for dipping.
