d52881
iHeat the vegetable oil in a large frying pan, and brown the beef all over.
i(You may need to do this in batches.
i) Set aside, then brown the kidneys on both sides in the same pan.
iAdd the onions and cook for 3-4 minutes.
iAdd the stock to the pan, stir well and bring to the boil.
iTurn the heat down and simmer for 1½ hours without a lid.
iIf the liquid evaporates too much, add more stock.
iRemove from the heat.
iAdd salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and allow to cool completely.
iPlace the cooked meat mixture into a pie dish.
iRoll out the pastry to 5mm/¼in thick and 5cm/2in larger than the dish you are using.
iUsing a rolling pin, lift the pastry and place it over the top of the pie dish.
iTrim and crimp the edges with your fingers and thumb.
iBrush the surface with the beaten egg mixture and bake for 30-40 minutes until golden-brown and puffed.
iServe with creamy mash and steamed vegetables to soak up the gravy.
