nVegetable Shepherd’s Pie
cBeef
d53000
iPreheat oven to 450°.
iBake potatoes on a foil-lined baking sheet until tender, about 45 minutes.
iLet cool slightly, then peel.
iPress potatoes through a ricer, food mill, or colander into a large bowl.
iAdd butter; stir until well blended.
iStir in milk.
iSeason to taste with salt.
iSoak dried porcini in 3 cups hot water; set aside.
iCombine lentils, 1 garlic clove, 1 tsp.
isalt, and 4 cups water in a medium saucepan.
iBring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until lentils are tender but not mushy, 15–20 minutes.
iDrain lentils and discard garlic.
iHeat 3 Tbsp.
ioil in a large heavy pot over medium heat.
iAdd onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, about 12 minutes.
iAdd chopped garlic and cook for 1 minute.
iStir in tomato paste.
iCook, stirring constantly, until tomato paste is caramelized, 2–3 minutes.
iAdd bay leaves and wine; stir, scraping up any browned bits.
iStir in porcini, slowly pouring porcini soaking liquid into pan but leaving any sediment behind.
iBring to a simmer and cook until liquid is reduced by half, about 10 minutes.
iStir in broth and cook, stirring occasionally, until reduced by half, about 45 minutes.
iStrain mixture into a large saucepan and bring to a boil; discard solids in strainer.
iStir cornstarch and 2 Tbsp.
iwater in a small bowl to dissolve.
iAdd cornstarch mixture; simmer until thickened, about 5 minutes.
iWhisk in miso.
iSeason sauce with salt and pepper.
iSet aside.
iPreheat oven to 450°.
iToss vegetables and pearl onions with remaining 2 Tbsp.
ioil, 5 garlic cloves, and rosemary sprigs in a large bowl; season with salt and pepper.
iDivide between 2 rimmed baking sheets.
iRoast, stirring once, until tender, 20–25 minutes.
iTransfer garlic cloves to a small bowl; mash well with a fork and stir into sauce.
iDiscard rosemary.
iDO AHEAD: Lentils, sauce, and vegetables can be made 1 day ahead.
iCover separately; chill.
iArrange lentils in an even layer in a 3-qt.
ibaking dish; set dish on a foil-lined rimmed baking sheet.
iToss roasted vegetables with fresh mushrooms and chopped herbs; layer on top of lentils.
iPour sauce over vegetables.
iSpoon potato mixture evenly over.
iBake until browned and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
iLet stand for 15 minutes before serving.
