nChicken Alfredo Primavera
cChicken
d52796
iHeat 1 tablespoon of butter and 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
iSeason both sides of each chicken breast with seasoned salt and a pinch of pepper.
iAdd the chicken to the skillet and cook for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.
iWhile the chicken is cooking, bring a large pot of water to a boil.
iSeason the boiling water with a few generous pinches of kosher salt.
iAdd the pasta and give it a stir.
iCook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, about 12 minutes.
iReserve 1/2 cup of  pasta water before draining the pasta.
iRemove the chicken from the pan and transfer it to a cutting board; allow it to rest.
iTurn the heat down to medium and dd the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter and olive oil to the same pan you used to cook the chicken.
iAdd the veggies (minus the garlic) and red pepper flakes to the pan and stir to coat with the oil and butter (refrain from seasoning with salt until the veggies are finished browning).
iCook, stirring often, until the veggies are tender, about 5 minutes.
iAdd the garlic and a generous pinch of salt and pepper to the pan and cook for 1 minute.
iDeglaze the pan with the white wine.
iContinue to cook until the wine has reduced by half, about 3 minutes.
iStir in the milk, heavy cream, and reserved pasta water.
iBring the mixture to a gentle boil and allow to simmer and reduce for 2-3 minutes.
iTurn off the heat and add the Parmesan cheese and cooked pasta.
iSeason with salt and pepper to taste.
iGarnish with Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley, if desired.
