nChicken Basquaise
cChicken
d52934
iPreheat the oven to 180°C/Gas mark 4.
iHave the chicken joints ready to cook.
iHeat the butter and 3 tbsp olive oil in a flameproof casserole or large frying pan.
iBrown the chicken pieces in batches on both sides, seasoning them with salt and pepper as you go.
iDon't crowd the pan - fry the chicken in small batches, removing the pieces to kitchen paper as they are done.
iAdd a little more olive oil to the casserole and fry the onions over a medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until softened but not browned.
iAdd the rest of the oil, then the peppers and cook for another 5 minutes.
iAdd the chorizo, sun-dried tomatoes and garlic and cook for 2-3 minutes.
iAdd the rice, stirring to ensure it is well coated in the oil.
iStir in the tomato paste, paprika, bay leaves and chopped thyme.
iPour in the stock and wine.
iWhen the liquid starts to bubble, turn the heat down to a gentle simmer.
iPress the rice down into the liquid if it isn't already submerged and place the chicken on top.
iAdd the lemon wedges and olives around the chicken.
iCover and cook in the oven for 50 minutes.
iThe rice should be cooked but still have some bite, and the chicken should have juices that run clear when pierced in the thickest part with a knife.
iIf not, cook for another 5 minutes and check again.
