nChicken Ham and Leek Pie
cChicken
d52875
iHeat the chicken stock in a lidded saucepan.
iAdd the chicken breast and bring to a low simmer.
iCover with a lid and cook for 10 minutes.
iRemove the chicken breasts from the water with tongs and place on a plate.
iPour the cooking liquor into a large jug.
iMelt 25g/1oz of the butter in a large heavy-based saucepan over a low heat.
iStir in the leeks and fry gently for two minutes, stirring occasionally until just softened.
iAdd the garlic and cook for a further minute.
iAdd the remaining butter and stir in the flour as soon as the butter has melted.
iCook for 30 seconds, stirring constantly.
iSlowly pour the milk into the pan, just a little at a time, stirring well between each adding.
iGradually add 250ml/10fl oz of the reserved stock and the wine, if using, stirring until the sauce is smooth and thickened slightly.
iBring to a gentle simmer and cook for 3 minutes.
iSeason the mixture, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
iRemove from the heat and stir in the cream.
iPour into a large bowl and cover the surface of the sauce with cling ilm to prevent a skin forming.
iSet aside to cool.
iPreheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.
iPut a baking tray in the oven to heat.
iFor the pastry, put the flour and butter in a food processor and blend on the pulse setting until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
iWith the motor running, add the beaten egg and water and blend until the mixture forms a ball.
iPortion off 250g/10oz of pastry for the lid.
iRoll the remaining pastry out on a lightly floured surface, turning the pastry frequently until around 5mm/¼in thick and 4cm/1½in larger than the pie dish.
iLift the pastry over the rolling pin and place it gently into the pie dish.
iPress the pastry firmly up the sides, making sure there are no air bubbles.
iLeave the excess pastry overhanging the sides.
iCut the chicken breasts into 3cm/1¼in pieces.
iStir the chicken, ham and leeks into the cooled sauce.
iPour the chicken filling into the pie dish.
iBrush the rim of the dish with beaten egg.
iRoll out the reserved pastry for the lid.
iCover the pie with the pastry lid and press the edges together firmly to seal.
iTrim any excess pastry.
iMake a small hole in the centre of the pie with the tip of a knife.
iGlaze the top of the pie with beaten egg.
iBake on the preheated tray in the centre of the oven for 35-40 minutes or until the pie is golden-brown all over and the filling is piping hot.
