nChicken Handi
cChicken
d52795
iTake a large pot or wok, big enough to cook all the chicken, and heat the oil in it.
iOnce the oil is hot, add sliced onion and fry them until deep golden brown.
iThen take them out on a plate and set aside.
iTo the same pot, add the chopped garlic and sauté for a minute.
iThen add the chopped tomatoes and cook until tomatoes turn soft.
iThis would take about 5 minutes.
iThen return the fried onion to the pot and stir.
iAdd ginger paste and sauté well.
iNow add the cumin seeds, half of the coriander seeds and chopped green chillies.
iGive them a quick stir.
iNext goes in the spices – turmeric powder and red chilli powder.
iSauté the spices well for couple of minutes.
iAdd the chicken pieces to the wok, season it with salt to taste and cook the chicken covered on medium-low heat until the chicken is almost cooked through.
iThis would take about 15 minutes.
iSlowly sautéing the chicken will enhance the flavor, so do not expedite this step by putting it on high heat.
iWhen the oil separates from the spices, add the beaten yogurt keeping the heat on lowest so that the yogurt doesn’t split.
iSprinkle the remaining coriander seeds and add half of the dried fenugreek leaves.
iMix well.
iFinally add the cream and give a final mix to combine everything well.
iSprinkle the remaining kasuri methi and garam masala and serve the chicken handi hot with naan or rotis.
