nChicken Karaage
cChicken
d52831
iAdd the ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sake and sugar to a bowl and whisk to combine.
iAdd the chicken, then stir to coat evenly.
iCover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
iAdd 1 inch of vegetable oil to a heavy bottomed pot and heat until the oil reaches 360 degrees F.
iLine a wire rack with 2 sheets of paper towels and get your tongs out.
iAdd a handful of chicken to the potato starch and toss to coat each piece evenly.
iFry the karaage in batches until the exterior is a medium brown and the chicken is cooked through.
iTransfer the fried chicken to the paper towel lined rack.
iIf you want the karaage to stay crispy longer, you can fry the chicken a second time, until it's a darker color after it's cooled off once.
iServe with lemon wedges.
