nCrock Pot Chicken Baked Tacos
cChicken
d52830
iPut the uncooked chicken breasts in the crock pot.
iPour the full bottle of salad dressing over the chicken.
iSprinkle the rest of the ingredients over the top and mix them in a bit with a spoon.
iCover your crock pot with the lid and cook on high for 4 hours.
iRemove all the chicken breasts from the crock pot and let cool.
iShred the chicken breasts and move to a glass bowl.
iPour most of the liquid over the shredded chicken.
iMake the guacamole sauce by mixing the avocado and green salsa together.
iPour the guacamole mixture through a strainer until smooth and transfer to a squeeze bottle.
iCut the tip off the lid of the squeeze bottle to make the opening more wide if needed.
iMake the sour cream sauce by mixing the sour cream and milk together until you get a more liquid sour cream sauce.
iTransfer to a squeeze bottle.
iIn a 9x 13 glass baking dish, fill all 12+ tacos with a layer of refried beans, cooked chicken and shredded cheese.
iBake at 450 for 10-15 minutes just until the cheese is melted and bubbling.
iOut of the oven top all the tacos with the sliced grape tomaotes, jalapeno and cilantro.
iFinish with a drizzle of guacamole and sour cream.
