nFrench Onion Chicken with Roasted Carrots & Mashed Potatoes
cChicken
d52996
iPreheat oven to 425 degrees.
iWash and dry all produce.
iTrim, peel, and cut carrots on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces.
iDice potatoes into ½-inch pieces.
iHalve, peel, and thinly slice onion.
iToss carrots on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
iRoast until browned and tender, 15-20 minutes.
iMeanwhile, place potatoes in a medium pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
iBring to a boil and cook until tender, 12-15 minutes.
iDrain and return potatoes to pot; cover to keep warm.
iWhile potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
iAdd onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and softened, 8-10 minutes.
iSprinkle with 1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4 servings).
iStir in stock concentrate and 2 TBSP water (¼ cup for 4); season with salt and pepper.
iCook until jammy, 2-3 minutes more.
iTurn off heat; transfer to a small bowl.
iWash out pan.
iPat chicken dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper.
iHeat a drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat.
iAdd chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes per side.
iIn the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top with caramelized onion and cheese.
iCover pan until cheese melts.
iHeat pot with drained potatoes over low heat; mash with sour cream, 2 TBSP butter (4 TBSP for 4 servings), salt, pepper, and a splash of water (or milk, for extra richness) until smooth.
iDivide chicken, roasted carrots, and mashed potatoes between plates.
