nHoney Balsamic Chicken with Crispy Broccoli & Potatoes
cChicken
d52993
i1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
iWash and dry all produce.
iCut potatoes into 1/2-inch-thick wedges.
iToss on one side of a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
i(For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.
i) Roast on top rack for 5 minutes (we'll add the broccoli then).
i2. Meanwhile, cut broccoli florets into bite-size pieces, if necessary.
iPeel and finely chop garlic.
iIn a small microwave-safe bowl, combine 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and half the garlic.
iMicrowave until garlic sizzles, 30 seconds.
i3. Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven and add broccoli to empty side; carefully toss with garlic oil, salt, and pepper.
i(For 4 servings, add broccoli to a second sheet.
i) Continue roasting until potatoes and broccoli are browned and crispy, 15-20 minutes more.
i4. While veggies roast, pat chicken dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper.
iHeat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
iAdd chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes per side.
i(If chicken browns too quickly, reduce heat to medium.
i) Turn off heat; set chicken aside to rest.
iWash out pan.
i5. Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.
iAdd a drizzle of oil and remaining garlic; cook until fragrant, 30 seconds.
iStir in vinegar, honey, stock concentrate, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings).
iSimmer until thick and glossy, 2-3 minutes.
iRemove from heat and stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4).
iSeason with salt and pepper.
i6. Return chicken to pan and turn to coat in glaze.
iDivide chicken, broccoli, and potatoes between plates.
iSpoon any remaining glaze over chicken and serve.
