nRappie Pie
cChicken
d52933
iPreheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
iGrease a 10x14x2-inch baking pan.
iHeat margarine in a skillet over medium heat; stir in onion.
iCook and stir until onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes.
iReduce heat to low and continue to cook and stir until onion is very tender and dark brown, about 40 minutes more.
iBring chicken broth to a boil in a large pot; stir in chicken breasts, reduce heat, and simmer until chicken is no longer pink at the center, about 20 minutes.
iRemove from heat.
iRemove chicken breasts to a plate using a slotted spoon; reserve broth.
iJuice potatoes with an electric juicer; place dry potato flesh into a bowl and discard juice.
iStir salt and pepper into potatoes; stir in enough reserved broth to make the mixture the consistency of oatmeal.
iSet remaining broth aside.
iSpread half of potato mixture evenly into the prepared pan.
iLay cooked chicken breast evenly over potatoes; scatter caramelized onion evenly over chicken.
iSpread remaining potato mixture over onions and chicken to cover.
iBake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 1 hour.
iReheat chicken broth; pour over individual servings as desired.
