nShawarma
cChicken
d53028
iCombine the marinade ingredients in a large ziplock bag (or bowl).
iAdd the chicken and use your hands to make sure each piece is coated.
iIf using a ziplock bag, I find it convenient to close the bag then massage the bag to disperse the rub all over each chicken piece.
iMarinate overnight or up to 24 hours.
iCombine the Yoghurt Sauce ingredients in a bowl and mix.
iCover and put in the fridge until required (it will last for 3 days in the fridge).
iHeat grill/BBQ (or large heavy based pan on stove) on medium high.
iYou should not need to oil it because the marinade has oil in it and also thigh fillets have fat.
iBut if you are worried then oil your hotplate/grill.
iPlace chicken on the grill and cook the first side for 4 to 5 minutes until nicely charred, then turn and cook the other side for 3 to 4 minutes (the 2nd side takes less time).
iRemove chicken from the grill and cover loosely with foil.
iSet aside to rest for 5 minutes.
iSlice chicken and pile onto platter alongside flatbreads, Salad and the Yoghurt Sauce.
iTo make a wrap, get a piece of flatbread and smear with Yoghurt Sauce.
iTop with a bit of lettuce and tomato and Chicken Shawarma.
