nTeriyaki Chicken Casserole
cChicken
d52772
iPreheat oven to 350° F.
iSpray a 9x13-inch baking pan with non-stick spray.
iCombine soy sauce, ½ cup water, brown sugar, ginger and garlic in a small saucepan and cover.
iBring to a boil over medium heat.
iRemove lid and cook for one minute once boiling.
iMeanwhile, stir together the corn starch and 2 tablespoons of water in a separate dish until smooth.
iOnce sauce is boiling, add mixture to the saucepan and stir to combine.
iCook until the sauce starts to thicken then remove from heat.
iPlace the chicken breasts in the prepared pan.
iPour one cup of the sauce over top of chicken.
iPlace chicken in oven and bake 35 minutes or until cooked through.
iRemove from oven and shred chicken in the dish using two forks.
i*Meanwhile, steam or cook the vegetables according to package directions.
iAdd the cooked vegetables and rice to the casserole dish with the chicken.
iAdd most of the remaining sauce, reserving a bit to drizzle over the top when serving.
iGently toss everything together in the casserole dish until combined.
iReturn to oven and cook 15 minutes.
iRemove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
iDrizzle each serving with remaining sauce.
