nThai Green Curry
cChicken
d52814
iPut the potatoes in a pan of boiling water and cook for 5 minutes.
iThrow in the beans and cook for a further 3 minutes, by which time both should be just tender but not too soft.
iDrain and put to one side.
iIn a wok or large frying pan, heat the oil until very hot, then drop in the garlic and cook until golden, this should take only a few seconds.
iDon’t let it go very dark or it will spoil the taste.
iSpoon in the curry paste and stir it around for a few seconds to begin to cook the spices and release all the flavours.
iNext, pour in the coconut milk and let it come to a bubble.
iStir in the fish sauce and sugar, then the pieces of chicken.
iTurn the heat down to a simmer and cook, covered, for about 8 minutes until the chicken is cooked.
iTip in the potatoes and beans and let them warm through in the hot coconut milk, then add a lovely citrussy flavour by stirring in the shredded lime leaves (or lime zest).
iThe basil leaves go in next, but only leave them briefly on the heat or they will quickly lose their brightness.
iScatter with the lime garnish and serve immediately with boiled rice.
