nApple & Blackberry Crumble
cDessert
d52893
iHeat oven to 190C/170C fan/gas 5.
iTip the flour and sugar into a large bowl.
iAdd the butter, then rub into the flour using your fingertips to make a light breadcrumb texture.
iDo not overwork it or the crumble will become heavy.
iSprinkle the mixture evenly over a baking sheet and bake for 15 mins or until lightly coloured.
iMeanwhile, for the compote, peel, core and cut the apples into 2cm dice.
iPut the butter and sugar in a medium saucepan and melt together over a medium heat.
iCook for 3 mins until the mixture turns to a light caramel.
iStir in the apples and cook for 3 mins.
iAdd the blackberries and cinnamon, and cook for 3 mins more.
iCover, remove from the heat, then leave for 2-3 mins to continue cooking in the warmth of the pan.
iTo serve, spoon the warm fruit into an ovenproof gratin dish, top with the crumble mix, then reheat in the oven for 5-10 mins.
iServe with vanilla ice cream.
