nApple Frangipan Tart
cDessert
d52768
iPreheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.
iPut the biscuits in a large re-sealable freezer bag and bash with a rolling pin into fine crumbs.
iMelt the butter in a small pan, then add the biscuit crumbs and stir until coated with butter.
iTip into the tart tin and, using the back of a spoon, press over the base and sides of the tin to give an even layer.
iChill in the fridge while you make the filling.
iCream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
iYou can do this in a food processor if you have one.
iProcess for 2-3 minutes.
iMix in the eggs, then add the ground almonds and almond extract and blend until well combined.
iPeel the apples, and cut thin slices of apple.
iDo this at the last minute to prevent the apple going brown.
iArrange the slices over the biscuit base.
iSpread the frangipane filling evenly on top.
iLevel the surface and sprinkle with the flaked almonds.
iBake for 20-25 minutes until golden-brown and set.
iRemove from the oven and leave to cool for 15 minutes.
iRemove the sides of the tin.
iAn easy way to do this is to stand the tin on a can of beans and push down gently on the edges of the tin.
iTransfer the tart, with the tin base attached, to a serving plate.
iServe warm with cream, crème fraiche or ice cream.
