nBakewell tart
cDessert
d52767
iTo make the pastry, measure the flour into a bowl and rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
iAdd the water, mixing to form a soft dough.
iRoll out the dough on a lightly floured work surface and use to line a 20cm/8in flan tin.
iLeave in the fridge to chill for 30 minutes.
iPreheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6 (180C fan).
iLine the pastry case with foil and fill with baking beans.
iBake blind for about 15 minutes, then remove the beans and foil and cook for a further five minutes to dry out the base.
iFor the filing, spread the base of the flan generously with raspberry jam.
iMelt the butter in a pan, take off the heat and then stir in the sugar.
iAdd ground almonds, egg and almond extract.
iPour into the flan tin and sprinkle over the flaked almonds.
iBake for about 35 minutes.
iIf the almonds seem to be browning too quickly, cover the tart loosely with foil to prevent them burning.
