nBattenberg Cake
cDessert
d52894
iHeat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4 and line the base and sides of a 20cm square tin with baking parchment (the easiest way is to cross 2 x 20cm-long strips over the base).
iTo make the almond sponge, put the butter, sugar, flour, ground almonds, baking powder, eggs, vanilla and almond extract in a large bowl.
iBeat with an electric whisk until the mix comes together smoothly.
iScrape into the tin, spreading to the corners, and bake for 25-30 mins – when you poke in a skewer, it should come out clean.
iCool in the tin for 10 mins, then transfer to a wire rack to finish cooling while you make the second sponge.
iFor the pink sponge, line the tin as above.
iMix all the ingredients together as above, but don’t add the almond extract.
iFold in some pink food colouring.
iThen scrape it all into the tin and bake as before.
iCool.
iTo assemble, heat the jam in a small pan until runny, then sieve.
iBarely trim two opposite edges from the almond sponge, then well trim a third edge.
iRoughly measure the height of the sponge, then cutting from the well-trimmed edge, use a ruler to help you cut 4 slices each the same width as the sponge height.
iDiscard or nibble leftover sponge.
iRepeat with pink cake.
iTake 2 x almond slices and 2 x pink slices and trim so they are all the same length.
iRoll out one marzipan block on a surface lightly dusted with icing sugar to just over 20cm wide, then keep rolling lengthways until the marzipan is roughly 0.
i5cm thick.
iBrush with apricot jam, then lay a pink and an almond slice side by side at one end of the marzipan, brushing jam in between to stick sponges, and leaving 4cm clear marzipan at the end.
iBrush more jam on top of the sponges, then sandwich remaining 2 slices on top, alternating colours to give a checkerboard effect.
iTrim the marzipan to the length of the cakes.
iCarefully lift up the marzipan and smooth over the cake with your hands, but leave a small marzipan fold along the bottom edge before you stick it to the first side.
iTrim opposite side to match size of fold, then crimp edges using fingers and thumb (or, more simply, press with prongs of fork).
iIf you like, mark the 10 slices using the prongs of a fork.
iAssemble second Battenberg and keep in an airtight box or well wrapped in cling film for up to 3 days.
iCan be frozen for up to a month.
