nBread and Butter Pudding
cDessert
d52792
iGrease a 1 litre/2 pint pie dish with butter.
iCut the crusts off the bread.
iSpread each slice with on one side with butter, then cut into triangles.
iArrange a layer of bread, buttered-side up, in the bottom of the dish, then add a layer of sultanas.
iSprinkle with a little cinnamon, then repeat the layers of bread and sultanas, sprinkling with cinnamon, until you have used up all of the bread.
iFinish with a layer of bread, then set aside.
iGently warm the milk and cream in a pan over a low heat to scalding point.
iDon't let it boil.
iCrack the eggs into a bowl, add three quarters of the sugar and lightly whisk until pale.
iAdd the warm milk and cream mixture and stir well, then strain the custard into a bowl.
iPour the custard over the prepared bread layers and sprinkle with nutmeg and the remaining sugar and leave to stand for 30 minutes.
iPreheat the oven to 180C/355F/Gas 4.
iPlace the dish into the oven and bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the custard has set and the top is golden-brown.
