nCanadian Butter Tarts
cDessert
d52923
iPreheat the oven to fan 170C/ conventional 190C/gas 5.
iRoll out the pastry on a lightly floured surface so it’s slightly thinner than straight from the pack.
iThen cut out 18-20 rounds with a 7.
i5cm fluted cutter, re-rolling the trimmings.
iUse the rounds to line two deep 12-hole tart tins (not muffin tins).
iIf you only have a regular-sized, 12-hole tart tin you will be able to make a few more slightly shallower tarts.
iBeat the eggs in a large bowl and combine with the rest of the ingredients except the walnuts.
iTip this mixture into a pan and stir continuously for 3-4 minutes until the butter melts, and the mixture bubbles and starts to thicken.
iIt should be thick enough to coat the back of a wooden spoon.
iDon’t overcook, and be sure to stir all the time as the mixture can easily burn.
iRemove from the heat and stir in the nuts.
iSpoon the filling into the unbaked tart shells so it’s level with the pastry.
iBake for 15-18 minutes until set and pale golden.
iLeave in the tin to cool for a few minutes before lifting out on to a wire rack.
iServe warm or cold.
