d52897
iFor the carrot cake, preheat the oven to 160C/325F/Gas 3.
iGrease and line a 26cm/10in springform cake tin.
iMix all of the ingredients for the carrot cake, except the carrots and walnuts, together in a bowl until well combined.
iStir in the carrots and walnuts.
iSpoon the mixture into the cake tin and bake for 1 hour 15 minutes, or until a skewer inserted into the middle comes out clean.
iRemove the cake from the oven and set aside to cool for 10 minutes, then carefully remove the cake from the tin and set aside to cool completely on a cooling rack.
iMeanwhile, for the icing, beat the cream cheese, caster sugar and butter together in a bowl until fluffy.
iSpread the icing over the top of the cake with a palette knife.
