nChocolate Souffle
cDessert
d52905
iHeat oven to 220C/fan 200C/gas 7 and place a baking tray on the top shelf.
iFor the sauce, heat the cream and sugar until boiling.
iRemove from the heat, stir in the chocolate and butter until melted, then keep warm.
iBrush 6 x 150ml ramekins with melted butter, sprinkle with the 2 tbsp caster sugar, then tip out any excess.
iMelt the chocolate and cream in a bowl over a pan of simmering water, cool, then mix in the egg yolks.
iWhisk the egg whites until they hold their shape, then add the sugar, 1 tbsp at a time, whisking back to the same consistency.
iMix a spoonful into the chocolate, then gently fold in the rest.
iWorking quickly, fill the ramekins, wipe the rims clean and run your thumb around the edges.
iTurn oven down to 200C/fan 180C/gas 6, place the ramekins onto the baking tray, then bake for 8-10 mins until risen with a slight wobble.
iDon’t open the oven door too early as this may make them collapse.
iOnce the soufflés are ready, dust with icing sugar, scoop a small hole from their tops, then pour in some of the hot chocolate sauce.
iReplace the lids and serve straight away.
