nChristmas cake
cDessert
d52990
iHeat oven to 160C/fan 140C/gas 3.
iLine the base and sides of a 20 cm round, 7.
i5 cm deep cake tin.
iBeat the butter and sugar with an electric hand mixer for 1-2 mins until very creamy and pale in colour, scraping down the sides of the bowl half way through.
iStir in a spoonful of the flour, then stir in the beaten egg and the rest of the flour alternately, a quarter at a time, beating well each time with a wooden spoon.
iStir in the almonds.
iMix in the sherry (the mix will look curdled), then add the peel, cherries, raisins, cherries, nuts, lemon zest, spice, rosewater and vanilla.
iBeat together to mix, then stir in the baking powder.
iSpoon mixture into the tin and smooth the top, making a slight dip in the centre.
iBake for 30 mins, then lower temperature to 150C/fan 130C/gas 2 and bake a further 2-2¼ hrs, until a skewer insterted in the middle comes out clean.
iLeave to cool in the tin, then take out of the tin and peel off the lining paper.
iWhen completely cold, wrap well in cling film and foil to store until ready to decorate.
iThe cake will keep for several months.
