nClassic Christmas pudding
cDessert
d52988
iGet everything for the pudding prepared.
iChop the almonds coarsely.
iPeel, core and chop the cooking apples.
iSharpen your knife and chop the candied peel.
i(You can chop the almonds and apples in a food processor, but the peel must be done by hand.
i) Grate three quarters of the nutmeg (sounds a lot but it's correct).
iMix the almonds, apples, candied peel, nutmeg, raisins, flour, breadcrumbs, light muscovado sugar, eggs and 2 tbsp brandy or cognac in a large bowl.
iHolding the butter in its wrapper, grate a quarter of it into the bowl, then stir everything together.
iRepeat until all the butter is grated, then stir for 3-4 mins – the mixture is ready when it subsides slightly after each stir.
iAsk the family to stir too, and get everyone to make a wish.
iGenerously butter two 1.
i2 litre bowls and put a circle of baking parchment in the bottom of each.
iPack in the pudding mixture.
iCover with a double layer of baking parchment, pleating it to allow for expansion, then tie with string (keep the paper in place with a rubber band while tying).
iTrim off any excess paper.
iNow stand each bowl on a large sheet of foil and bring the edges up over the top, then put another sheet of foil over the top and bring it down underneath to make a double package (this makes the puddings watertight).
iTie with more string, and make a handle for easy lifting in and out of the pan.
iWatch our video to see how to tie up a pudding correctly.
iBoil or oven steam the puddings for 8 hrs, topping up with water as necessary.
iRemove from the pans and leave to cool overnight.
iWhen cold, discard the messy wrappings and re-wrap in new baking parchment, foil and string.
iStore in a cool, dry place until Christmas.
iTo make the brandy butter, cream the butter with the orange zest and icing sugar.
iGradually beat in the brandy or cognac and chopped stem ginger.
iPut in a small bowl, fork the top attractively and put in the fridge to set.
iThe butter will keep for a week in the fridge, or it can be frozen for up to six weeks.
iOn Christmas Day, boil or oven steam for 1 hr.
iUnwrap and turn out.
iTo flame, warm 3-4 tbsp brandy in a small pan, pour it over the pudding and set light to it.
