nHot Chocolate Fudge
cDessert
d52787
iLine an 8-inch-square baking pan with wax paper or foil, and coat with non-stick spray.
iIn a microwave-safe bowl, combine the dark chocolate chips, heavy cream and half of the sweetened condensed milk.
iMicrowave the dark chocolate mixture in 20-second intervals, stirring in between each interval, until the chocolate is melted.
iAdd the vanilla extract to the dark chocolate mixture and stir well until smooth.
iTransfer the dark chocolate mixture into the prepared pan and spread into an even layer.
iIn a separate bowl, combine the white chocolate chips with the remaining half of the sweetened condensed milk.
iMicrowave the white chocolate mixture in 20-second intervals, stirring in between each interval, until the chocolate is melted.
iEvenly spread the white chocolate mixture on top of dark chocolate layer.
iTop the chocolate layers with the Mallow Bits or miniature marshmallows, and gently press them down.
iRefrigerate for 4 hours, or until set.
iRemove the fudge and wax paper from the pan.
iCarefully peel all of the wax paper from the fudge.
iCut the fudge into bite-sized pieces and serve.
