nKey Lime Pie
cDessert
d52859
iHeat the oven to 160C/fan 140C/gas 3.
iWhizz the biscuits to crumbs in a food processor (or put in a strong plastic bag and bash with a rolling pin).
iMix with the melted butter and press into the base and up the sides of a 22cm loose-based tart tin.
iBake in the oven for 10 minutes.
iRemove and cool.
iPut the egg yolks in a large bowl and whisk for a minute with electric beaters.
iAdd the condensed milk and whisk for 3 minutes then add the zest and juice and whisk again for 3 minutes.
iPour the filling into the cooled base then put back in the oven for 15 minutes.
iCool then chill for at least 3 hours or overnight if you like.
iWhen you are ready to serve, carefully remove the pie from the tin and put on a serving plate.
iTo decorate, softly whip together the cream and icing sugar.
iDollop or pipe the cream onto the top of the pie and finish with extra lime zest.
