nKrispy Kreme Donut
cDessert
d53015
iDissolve yeast in warm water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
iAdd milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
iBeat on low for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
iBeat on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
iStir in remaining flour until smooth.
iCover and let rise until double, 50-60 minutes.
i(Dough is ready when indentation remains when touched.
i) Turn dough onto floured surface; roll around lightly to coat with flour.
iGently roll dough 1/2-inch thick with floured rolling pin.
iCut with floured doughnut cutter.
iCover and let rise until double, 30-40 minutes.
iHeat vegetable oil in deep fryer to 350°.
iSlide doughnuts into hot oil with wide spatula.
iTurn doughnuts as they rise to the surface.
iFry until golden brown, about 1 minute on each side.
iRemove carefully from oil (do not prick surface); drain.
iDip the doughnuts into creamy glaze set on rack.
iHeat butter until melted.
iRemove from heat.
iStir in powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
iStir in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until desired consistency.
