nMadeira Cake
cDessert
d52900
iPre-heat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.
iGrease an 18cm/7in round cake tin, line the base with greaseproof paper and grease the paper.
iCream the butter and sugar together in a bowl until pale and fluffy.
iBeat in the eggs, one at a time, beating the mixture well between each one and adding a tablespoon of the flour with the last egg to prevent the mixture curdling.
iSift the flour and gently fold in, with enough milk to give a mixture that falls slowly from the spoon.
iFold in the lemon zest.
iSpoon the mixture into the prepared tin and lightly level the top.
iBake on the middle shelf of the oven for 30-40 minutes, or until golden-brown on top and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean.
iRemove from the oven and set aside to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out on to a wire rack and leave to cool completely.
iTo serve, decorate the cake with the candied peel.
