nPeanut Butter Cheesecake
cDessert
d52861
iOil and line a 20cm round loose- bottomed cake tin with cling film, making it as smooth as possible.
iMelt the butter in a pan.
iCrush the biscuits by bashing them in a bag with a rolling pin, then stir them into the butter until very well coated.
iPress the mixture firmly into the base of the tin and chill.
iSoak the gelatine in water while you make the filling.
iTip the ricotta into a bowl, then beat in the peanut butter and syrup.
iRicotta has a slightly grainy texture so blitz until smooth with a stick blender for a smoother texture if you prefer.
iTake the soaked gelatine from the water and squeeze dry.
iPut it into a pan with the milk and heat very gently until the gelatine dissolves.
iBeat into the peanut mixture, then tip onto the biscuit base.
iChill until set.
iTo freeze, leave in the tin and as soon as it is solid, cover the surface with cling film, then wrap the tin with cling film and foil.
iTo defrost, thaw in the fridge overnight.
iTo serve, carefully remove from the tin.
iWhisk the cream with the sugar until it holds its shape, then spread on top of the cheesecake and scatter with the peanut brittle.
