nPortuguese custard tarts
cDessert
d53046
iMix the flour and icing sugar, and use this to dust the work surface.
iRoll the pastry out to make a 45 x 30cm rectangle.
iRoll up lengthways to create a long sausage shape.
iCut the pastry into 24 wheels, about 1-2cm thick.
iRoll each wheel lightly with the rolling pin to fit 2 x 12-hole non-stick fairy cake tins.
iPress the pastry circles into the tins and mould into the tins to make thin cases.
iChill until needed.
iHeat the oven to 220C/fan 200C/gas 7.
iMake a sugar syrup by bringing the sugar, 200ml water, lemon zest and cinnamon stick to the boil.
iReduce until syrupy, allow to cool, then remove the cinnamon and lemon.
iWhisk the eggs, egg yolks and cornflour until smooth in another large pan.
iHeat the milk and vanilla pod seeds in a separate pan until just below the boil.
iGradually pour the hot milk over the eggs and cornflour, then cook on a low heat, continually whisking.
iAdd the cooled sugar syrup to the custard and whisk until thickened slightly.
iPour the custard through a sieve.
iPour into the pastry cases and bake for 15 minutes until the pastry is golden and the custard has darkened.
iCool completely in the tins then sift over icing sugar and ground cinnamon to serve.
