nPumpkin Pie
cDessert
d52857
iPlace the pumpkin in a large saucepan, cover with water and bring to the boil.
iCover with a lid and simmer for 15 mins or until tender.
iDrain pumpkin; let cool.
iHeat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4.
iRoll out the pastry on a lightly floured surface and use it to line a 22cm loose-bottomed tart tin.
iChill for 15 mins.
iLine the pastry with baking parchment and baking beans, then bake for 15 mins.
iRemove the beans and paper, and cook for a further 10 mins until the base is pale golden and biscuity.
iRemove from the oven and allow to cool slightly.
iIncrease oven to 220C/200C fan/gas 7.
iPush the cooled pumpkin through a sieve into a large bowl.
iIn a separate bowl, combine the sugar, salt, nutmeg and half the cinnamon.
iMix in the beaten eggs, melted butter and milk, then add to the pumpkin purée and stir to combine.
iPour into the tart shell and cook for 10 mins, then reduce the temperature to 180C/160C fan/gas 4.
iContinue to bake for 35-40 mins until the filling has just set.
iLeave to cool, then remove the pie from the tin.
iMix the remaining cinnamon with the icing sugar and dust over the pie.
iServe chilled.
