nSpotted Dick
cDessert
d52886
iPut the flour and salt in a bowl.
iAdd the suet, currants, sugar, lemon and orange zest.
iPour in 150ml milk and mix to a firm but moist dough, adding the extra milk if necessary.
iShape into a fat roll about 20cm long.
iPlace on a large rectangle of baking parchment.
iWrap loosely to allow for the pudding to rise and tie the ends with string like a Christmas cracker.
iPlace a steamer over a large pan of boiling water, add the pudding to the steamer, cover and steam for 1 1/2 hours.
iTop up the pan with water from time to time.
iRemove from the steamer and allow to cool slightly before unwrapping.
iServe sliced with custard.
