nSticky Toffee Pudding
cDessert
d52883
iPreheat the oven to 180C/160C Fan/Gas 4.
iButter a wide shallow 1.
i7-litre/3-pint ovenproof dish.
iPut the butter, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and treacle into a mixing bowl.
iBeat using an electric handheld whisk for about 30 seconds or until combined.
iPour in the milk gradually and whisk again until smooth.
iPour into the prepared dish.
iBake for 35–40 minutes or until well risen and springy in the centre.
iTo make the sauce, put all the ingredients into a saucepan and stir over a low heat until the sugar has dissolved and the butter has melted.
iBring to the boil, stirring for a minute.
iTo serve, pour half the sauce over the pudding in the baking dish.
iServe with the cream or ice cream.
