d52805
iGrind the cashew, poppy seeds and cumin seeds into a smooth paste, using as little water as possible.
iSet aside.
iDeep fry the sliced onions when it is hot.
iDon’t overcrowd the oil.
iWhen the onions turn light brown, remove from oil and drain on paper towel.
iThe fried onion will crisp up as it drains.
iAlso fry the cashewnuts till golden brown.
iSet aside.
iWash the rice and soak in water for twenty minutes.
iMeanwhile, take a big wide pan, add oil in medium heat, add the sliced onions, add the blended paste, to it add the green chillies, ginger garlic paste and garlic and fry for a minute.
iThen add the tomatoes and sauté them well till they are cooked and not mushy.
iThen to it add the red chilli powder, biryani powder, mint, coriander leaves and sauté them well.
iAdd the yogurt and mix well.
iI always move the skillet away from the heat when adding yogurt which prevents it from curdling.
iNow after returning the skillet back to the stove, add the washed lamb and salt and ½ cup water and mix well.
iCook for 1 hour and cook it covered in medium low heat or put it in a pressure cooker for 6 whistles.
iIf the water is not drained totally, heat it by keeping it open.
iTake another big pan, add thrice the cup of rice you use, and boil it.
iWhen it is boiling high, add the rice, salt and jeera and mix well.
iAfter 7 minutes exact or when the rice is 80% done.
iSwitch off and drain the rice.
iNow, the layering starts.
iTo the lamb, pat and level it.
iAdd the drained hot rice on the top of it.
iGarnish with fried onions, ghee, mint, coriander leaves and saffron dissolved in milk.
iCover the dish and bake in a 350f oven for 15 minutes or till the cooked but not mushy.
iOr cook in the stove medium heat for 12 minutes and lowest heat for 5 minutes.
iAnd switch off.
i1. If you are cooking in oven, do make sure to cook in a big oven safe pan and cover it tight and then keep in oven for the final step.
i3. If it is spicy in the end, squeeze some lemon, it will reduce the heat and enhance the flavors also.
