nLamb Tagine
cLamb
d52843
iHeat the olive oil in a heavy-based pan and add the onion and carrot.
iCook for 3- 4 mins until softened.
iAdd the diced lamb and brown all over.
iStir in the garlic and all the spices and cook for a few mins more or until the aromas are released.
iAdd the honey and apricots, crumble in the stock cube and pour over roughly 500ml boiling water or enough to cover the meat.
iGive it a good stir and bring to the boil.
iTurn down to a simmer, put the lid on and cook for 1 hour.
iRemove the lid and cook for a further 30 mins, then stir in the squash.
iCook for 20 – 30 mins more until the squash is soft and the lamb is tender.
iServe alongside rice or couscous and sprinkle with parsley and pine nuts, if using.
