nRigatoni with fennel sausage sauce
cLamb
d52783
iHeat a tablespoon of oil in a large saute pan for which you have a lid.
iAdd the sausage pieces and fry on a medium-high heat for 10 minutes, stirring regularly, until golden-brown all over.
iTransfer the sausages to a plate, then add the onion and fennel to the hot pan and fry for 15 minutes, stirring once in a while, until soft and caramelised; if the pan goes a bit dry, add a teaspoon or so of extra oil.
iStir in the paprika, garlic and half the fennel seeds, fry for two minutes more, then pour on the wine and boil for 30 seconds, to reduce by half.
iAdd the tomatoes, sugar, 100ml water, the seared sausage and half a teaspoon of salt, cover and simmer for 30 minutes; remove the lid after 10 minutes, and cook until the sauce is thick and rich.
iRemove from the heat, stir through the olives and remaining fennel seeds and set aside until you’re ready to serve.
iBring a large pot of salted water to a boil, add the pasta and cook for 12-14 minutes (or according to the instructions on the packet), until al dente.
iMeanwhile, reheat the sauce.
iDrain the pasta, return it to the pot, stir in a tablespoon of oil, then divide between the bowls.
iPut all the pesto ingredients except the basil in the small bowl of a food processor.
iAdd a tablespoon of water and blitz to a rough paste.
iAdd the basil, then blitz until just combined (the pesto has a much better texture if the basil is not overblended).
iSpoon over the ragù and top with a spoonful of pesto.
iFinish with a sprinkling of chopped fennel fronds, if you have any, and serve at once.
