nCallaloo Jamaican Style
cMiscellaneous
d52939
iCut leaves and soft stems from the kale branches, them soak in a bowl of cold water for about 5-10 minutes or until finish with prep.
iProceed to slicing the onions, mincing the garlic and dicing the tomatoes.
iRemove kale from water cut in chunks.
iPlace bacon on saucepan and cook until crispy.
iAdd tomatoes; scotch bonnet pepper, smoked paprika.
iSauté for about 2-3 more minutes.
iFinally add vegetable, salt, mix well, and steamed for about 6-8 minutes or until leaves are tender.
iAdd a tiny bit of water as needed.
iAdjust seasonings and turn off the heat.
iUsing a sharp knife cut both ends off the plantain.
iThis will make it easy to grab the skin of the plantains.
iSlit a shallow line down the long seam of the plantain; peel only as deep as the peel.
iRemove plantain peel by pulling it back.
iSlice the plantain into medium size lengthwise slices and set aside.
iCoat a large frying pan with cooking oil spray.
iSpray the tops of the plantains with a generous layer of oil spray and sprinkle with salt, freshly ground pepper.
iLet the plantains "fry" on medium heat, shaking the frying pan to redistribute them every few minutes.
iAs the plantains brown, continue to add more cooking oil spray, salt and pepper (if needed) until they have reached the desired color and texture.
