nChakchouka 
cMiscellaneous
d52969
iIn a large cast iron skillet or sauté pan with a lid, heat oil over medium high heat.
iAdd the onion and sauté for 2-3 minutes, until softened.
iAdd the peppers and garlic, and sauté for an additional 3-5 minutes.
iAdd the tomatoes, cumin, paprika, salt, and chili powder.
iMix well and bring the mixture to a simmer.
iReduce the heat to medium low and continue to simmer, uncovered, 10-15 minutes until the mixture has thickened to your desired consistency.
i(Taste the sauce at this point and adjust for salt and spice, as desired.
i) Using the back of a spoon, make four craters in the mixture, large enough to hold an egg.
iCrack one egg into each of the craters.
iCover the skillet and simmer for 5-7 minutes, until the eggs have set.
iServe immediately with crusty bread or pita.
