nFrench Lentils With Garlic and Thyme
cMiscellaneous
d52815
iPlace a large saucepan over medium heat and add oil.
iWhen hot, add chopped vegetables and sauté until softened, 5 to 10 minutes.
iAdd 6 cups water, lentils, thyme, bay leaves and salt.
iBring to a boil, then reduce to a fast simmer.
iSimmer lentils until they are tender and have absorbed most of the water, 20 to 25 minutes.
iIf necessary, drain any excess water after lentils have cooked.
iServe immediately, or allow them to cool and reheat later.
iFor a fuller taste, use some chicken stock and reduce the water by the same amount.
