nTurkey Meatloaf
cMiscellaneous
d52845
iHeat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4.
iHeat the oil in a large frying pan and cook the onion for 8-10 mins until softened.
iAdd the garlic, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tsp tomato purée, and stir until combined.
iSet aside to cool.
iPut the turkey mince, egg, breadcrumbs and cooled onion mix in a large bowl and season well.
iMix everything to combine, then shape into a rectangular loaf and place in a large roasting tin.
iSpread 2 tbsp barbecue sauce over the meatloaf and bake for 30 mins.
iMeanwhile, drain 1 can of beans only, then pour both cans into a large bowl.
iAdd the remaining barbecue sauce and tomato purée.
iSeason and set aside.
iWhen the meatloaf has had its initial cooking time, scatter the beans around the outside and bake for 15 mins more until the meatloaf is cooked through and the beans are piping hot.
iScatter over the parsley and serve the meatloaf in slices.
