nChilli prawn linguine
cPasta
d52839
iMix the dressing ingredients in a small bowl and season with salt and pepper.
iSet aside.
iCook the pasta according to the packet instructions.
iAdd the sugar snap peas for the last minute or so of cooking time.
iMeanwhile, heat the oil in a wok or large frying pan, toss in the garlic and chilli and cook over a fairly gentle heat for about 30 seconds without letting the garlic brown.
iTip in the prawns and cook over a high heat, stirring frequently, for about 3 minutes until they turn pink.
iAdd the tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes until they just start to soften.
iDrain the pasta and sugar snaps well, then toss into the prawn mixture.
iTear in the basil leaves, stir, and season with salt and pepper.
iServe with salad leaves drizzled with the lime dressing, and warm crusty bread.
