nFettucine alfredo
cPasta
d52835
iIn a medium saucepan, stir the clotted cream, butter and cornflour over a low-ish heat and bring to a low simmer.
iTurn off the heat and keep warm.
iMeanwhile, put the cheese and nutmeg in a small bowl and add a good grinding of black pepper, then stir everything together (don’t add any salt at this stage).
iPut the pasta in another pan with 2 tsp salt, pour over some boiling water and cook following pack instructions (usually 3-4 mins).
iWhen cooked, scoop some of the cooking water into a heatproof jug or mug and drain the pasta, but not too thoroughly.
iAdd the pasta to the pan with the clotted cream mixture, then sprinkle over the cheese and gently fold everything together over a low heat using a rubber spatula.
iWhen combined, splash in 3 tbsp of the cooking water.
iAt first, the pasta will look wet and sloppy: keep stirring until the water is absorbed and the sauce is glossy.
iCheck the seasoning before transferring to heated bowls.
iSprinkle over some chives or parsley, then serve immediately.
