nLasagne
cPasta
d52844
iHeat the oil in a large saucepan.
iUse kitchen scissors to snip the bacon into small pieces, or use a sharp knife to chop it on a chopping board.
iAdd the bacon to the pan and cook for just a few mins until starting to turn golden.
iAdd the onion, celery and carrot, and cook over a medium heat for 5 mins, stirring occasionally, until softened.
iAdd the garlic and cook for 1 min, then tip in the mince and cook, stirring and breaking it up with a wooden spoon, for about 6 mins until browned all over.
iStir in the tomato purée and cook for 1 min, mixing in well with the beef and vegetables.
iTip in the chopped tomatoes.
iFill each can half full with water to rinse out any tomatoes left in the can, and add to the pan.
iAdd the honey and season to taste.
iSimmer for 20 mins.
iHeat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6.
iTo assemble the lasagne, ladle a little of the ragu sauce into the bottom of the roasting tin or casserole dish, spreading the sauce all over the base.
iPlace 2 sheets of lasagne on top of the sauce overlapping to make it fit, then repeat with more sauce and another layer of pasta.
iRepeat with a further 2 layers of sauce and pasta, finishing with a layer of pasta.
iPut the crème fraîche in a bowl and mix with 2 tbsp water to loosen it and make a smooth pourable sauce.
iPour this over the top of the pasta, then top with the mozzarella.
iSprinkle Parmesan over the top and bake for 25–30 mins until golden and bubbling.
iServe scattered with basil, if you like.
