nBBQ Pork Sloppy Joes
cPork
d52995
iPreheat oven to 450 degrees.
iWash and dry all produce.
iCut sweet potatoes into ½-inch-thick wedges.
iToss on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
iRoast until browned and tender, 20-25 minutes.
iMeanwhile, halve and peel onion.
iSlice as thinly as possible until you have ¼ cup (½ cup for 4 servings); finely chop remaining onion.
iPeel and finely chop garlic.
iHalve lime; squeeze juice into a small bowl.
iHalve buns.
iAdd 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4) to a separate small microwave-safe bowl; microwave until melted, 30 seconds.
iBrush onto cut sides of buns.
iTo bowl with lime juice, add sliced onion, ¼ tsp sugar (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt.
iStir to combine; set aside to quick-pickle.
iHeat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
iAdd chopped onion and season with salt and pepper.
iCook, stirring, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
iAdd garlic and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds more.
iAdd pork and season with salt and pepper.
iCook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes.
iWhile pork cooks, in a third small bowl, combine BBQ sauce, pickling liquid from onion, 3 TBSP ketchup (6 TBSP for 4 servings), ½ tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4), and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4).
iOnce pork is cooked through, add BBQ sauce mixture to pan.
iCook, stirring, until sauce is thickened, 2-3 minutes.
iTaste and season with salt and pepper.
iMeanwhile, toast buns in oven or toaster oven until golden, 3-5 minutes.
iDivide toasted buns between plates and fill with as much BBQ pork as you’d like.
iTop with pickled onion and hot sauce.
iServe with sweet potato wedges on the side.
