nBigos (Hunters Stew)
cPork
d53018
iPreheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
iHeat a large pot over medium heat.
iAdd the bacon and kielbasa; cook and stir until the bacon has rendered its fat and sausage is lightly browned.
iUse a slotted spoon to remove the meat and transfer to a large casserole or Dutch oven.
iCoat the cubes of pork lightly with flour and fry them in the bacon drippings over medium-high heat until golden brown.
iUse a slotted spoon to transfer the pork to the casserole.
iAdd the garlic, onion, carrots, fresh mushrooms, cabbage and sauerkraut.
iReduce heat to medium; cook and stir until the carrots are soft, about 10 minutes.
iDo not let the vegetables brown.
iDeglaze the pan by pouring in the red wine and stirring to loosen all of the bits of food and flour that are stuck to the bottom.
iSeason with the bay leaf, basil, marjoram, paprika, salt, pepper, caraway seeds and cayenne pepper; cook for 1 minute.
iMix in the dried mushrooms, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, beef stock, tomato paste and tomatoes.
iHeat through just until boiling.
iPour the vegetables and all of the liquid into the casserole dish with the meat.
iCover with a lid.
iBake in the preheated oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until meat is very tender.
