nBoxty Breakfast
cPork
d53036
iBefore you start, put your oven on its lowest setting, ready to keep things warm.
iPeel the potatoes, grate 2 of them, then set aside.
iCut the other 2 into large chunks, then boil for 10-15 mins or until tender.
iMeanwhile, squeeze as much of the liquid from the grated potatoes as you can using a clean tea towel.
iMash the boiled potatoes, then mix with the grated potato, spring onions and flour.
iWhisk the egg white in a large bowl until it holds soft peaks.
iFold in the buttermilk, then add the bicarbonate of soda.
iFold into the potato mix.
iHeat a large non-stick frying pan over a medium heat, then add 1 tbsp butter and some of the oil.
iDrop 3-4 spoonfuls of the potato mixture into the pan, then gently cook for 3-5 mins on each side until golden and crusty.
iKeep warm on a plate in the oven while you cook the next batch, adding more butter and oil to the pan before you do so.
iYou will get 16 crumpet-size boxty from the mix.
iCan be made the day ahead, drained on kitchen paper, then reheated in a low oven for 20 mins.
iHeat the grill to medium and put the tomatoes in a heavy-based pan.
iAdd a good knob of butter and a little oil, then fry for about 5 mins until softened.
iGrill the bacon, then pile onto a plate and keep warm.
iStack up the boxty, bacon and egg, and serve the tomatoes on the side.
