nCrispy Sausages and Greens
cPork
d52999
iPreheat the oven to 350°.
iRemove the stems from one bunch of Tuscan kale and tear the leaves into 1" pieces (mustard greens, collards, spinach, and chard are great, too).
iCoarsely chop half a head of green cabbage.
iCombine the greens in a large baking dish and add 4 cloves of thinly sliced garlic.
iAdding some sliced onions and shiitake mushrooms at this point is optional, but highly recommended (I'll sauté the onions and mushrooms in a cast iron baking dish right on the stove before adding to the greens).
iCoat the greens with some olive oil and pour ½ cup chicken stock or broth over everything.
iCover the dish with foil and bake until the greens are wilted, about 15 minutes.
iRemove foil and season with salt and pepper.
iContinue to bake until cabbage is tender, about 20-25 minutes more.
iMeanwhile, heat a little olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high.
iPrick four sweet Italian sausages with a fork and cook until browned on all sides and cooked through, 10 to 12 minutes.
iWhen the greens are done, slice the sausage and toss into the greens with a splash of your favorite vinegar (I like sherry or red wine).
