nPork Cassoulet
cPork
d52847
iHeat oven to 140C/120C fan/gas 1.
iPut a large ovenproof pan (with a tight-fitting lid) on a high heat.
iAdd your fat and diced meat, cook for a few mins to seal the edges, giving it a quick stir to cook evenly.
iReduce the heat to low, add the sliced onion, whole garlic cloves, carrot and fennel seeds, and cook gently to soften the veg for a few mins.
iPour over the red wine vinegar, scraping any meaty bits off the bottom of the pan.
iAdd the stock, tomato purée, and half the rosemary and parsley.
iBring to the boil and simmer for 10 mins, then season, cover with a lid and put into the oven for 2 hrs, removing the lid for the final hour of cooking.
iStir occasionally and add the beans with 30 mins to go.
iRemove the pan from the oven and heat the grill.
iScatter the top with the remaining herbs and breadcrumbs, drizzle a little oil over the top, and return to the oven for 5-10 mins, until the breadcrumbs are golden.
iServe with crusty bread and green veg.
