nSkillet Apple Pork Chops with Roasted Sweet Potatoes & Zucchini
cPork
d52994
iAdjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees.
iWash and dry all produce.
iDice sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
iToss on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
iRoast on top rack for 12 minutes (we'll roast the zucchini then).
iMeanwhile, halve and core apple; thinly slice into half-moons.
iPeel and finely chop garlic.
iQuarter lemon.
iTrim and halve zucchini lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick half-moons.
iToss on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.
iSet aside.
iPat pork dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper.
iHeat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.
iAdd pork and cook until browned and cooked through, 4-5 minutes per side.
iTurn off heat; transfer to a plate.
iOnce sweet potatoes have roasted 12 minutes, transfer baking sheet with zucchini to middle rack and continue roasting until both veggies are browned and softened, 12-15 minutes more.
iMeanwhile, melt 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for pork over medium-high heat.
iAdd apple and season with salt and pepper.
iCook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until apple is slightly softened, 2-3 minutes.
iAdd garlic; cook until fragrant, 30 seconds.
iAdd 1/z cup water (3/4 cup for 4), stock concentrate, and 11/2 tsp sugar (3 tsp for 4).
iCook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and apple is very tender, 3-5 minutes.
iSeason with salt and pepper.
iRemove pan with apple from heat; stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and a squeeze of lemon juice.
iDivide pork, zucchini, and sweet potatoes between plates.
iTop pork with glazed apple sauce.
iTop zucchini with a squeeze of lemon juice.
