nStamppot
cPork
d52980
iWash and peel the potatoes and cut into similarly sized pieces for even cooking.
iIn a large soup pot, boil the potatoes and the bay leaves in salted water for 20 minutes.
iDiscard the bay leaves.
iIf you're not using a bag of ready-cut curly kale, wash the bunches thoroughly under cool running water to get rid of all soil—you wouldn't want that gritty texture in your finished dish.
iTrim any coarse stems and discard any brown leaves.
iWith a sharp knife, cut the curly kale into thin strips.
iPeel and chop the shallots.
iIn a frying pan or skillet, melt 1 tbsp.
iof butter and saute the shallots for a few minutes before adding the curly kale and 2 tbsp.
iof water.
