nTourtiere
cPork
d52926
iHeat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6.
iBoil the potato until tender, drain and mash, then leave to cool.
iHeat the oil in a non-stick pan, add the mince and onion and quickly fry until browned.
iAdd the garlic, spices, stock, plenty of pepper and a little salt and mix well.
iRemove from the heat, stir into the potato and leave to cool.
iRoll out half the pastry and line the base of a 20-23cm pie plate or flan tin.
iFill with the pork mixture and brush the edges of the pastry with water.
iRoll out the remaining dough and cover the pie.
iPress the edges of the pastry to seal, trimming off the excess.
iPrick the top of the pastry case to allow steam to escape and glaze the top with the beaten egg.
iBake for 30 mins until the pastry is crisp and golden.
iServe cut into wedges with a crisp green salad.
iLeftovers are good cold for lunch the next day, served with a selection of pickles.
