nFish pie
cSeafood
d52802
i01.
iPut the potatoes in a large pan of cold salted water and bring to the boil.
iLower the heat, cover, then simmer gently for 15 minutes until tender.
iDrain, then return to the pan over a low heat for 30 seconds to drive off any excess water.
iMash with 1 tbsp olive oil, then season.
i02.
iMeanwhile put the milk in a large sauté pan, add the fish and bring to the boil.
iRemove from the heat, cover and stand for 3 minutes.
iRemove the fish (reserving the milk) and pat dry with kitchen paper, then gently flake into an ovenproof dish, discarding the skin and any bones.
i03.
iHeat the remaining oil in a pan, stir in the flour and cook for 30 seconds.
iGradually stir in 200-250ml of the reserved milk (discard the rest).
iGrate in nutmeg, season, then bubble until thick.
iStir in the cream.
i04.
iPreheat the oven to 190°C/fan170°C/gas 5.
iGrate the artichokes and add to the dish with the leek, prawns and herbs.
iStir the lemon zest and juice into the sauce, then pour over.
iMix gently with a wooden spoon.
i05.
iSpoon the mash onto the fish mixture, then use a fork to make peaks, which will crisp and brown as it cooks.
iSprinkle over the cheese, then bake for 35-40 minutes until golden and bubbling.
iServe with wilted greens.
