nGarides Saganaki
cSeafood
d52764
iPlace the prawns in a pot and add enough water to cover.
iBoil for 5 minutes.
iDrain, reserving the liquid, and set aside.
iHeat 2 tablespoons of oil in a saucepan.
iAdd the onion; cook and stir until soft.
iMix in the parsley, wine, tomatoes, garlic and remaining olive oil.
iSimmer, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes, or until the sauce is thickened.
iWhile the sauce is simmering, the prawns should become cool enough to handle.
iFirst remove the legs by pinching them, and then pull off the shells, leaving the head and tail on.
iWhen the sauce has thickened, stir in the prawns.
iBring to a simmer again if the sauce has cooled with the prawns, and cook for about 5 minutes.
iAdd the feta and remove from the heat.
iLet stand until the cheese starts to melt.
iServe warm with slices of crusty bread.
iThough completely untraditional, you can add a few tablespoons of stock or passata to this recipe to make a delicious pasta sauce.
iToss with pasta after adding the feta, and serve.
