nKedgeree
cSeafood
d52887
iFor the rice, heat the oil in a large, lidded pan, add the onion, then gently fry for 5 mins until softened but not coloured.
iAdd the spices, season with salt, then continue to fry until the mix start to go brown and fragrant; about 3 mins.
iAdd the rice and stir in well.
iAdd 600ml water, stir, then bring to the boil.
iReduce to a simmer, then cover for 10 mins.
iTake off the heat and leave to stand, covered, for 10-15 mins more.
iThe rice will be perfectly cooked if you do not lift the lid before the end of the cooking.
iMeanwhile, put the haddock and bay leaves in a frying pan, cover with the milk, then poach for 10 mins until the flesh flakes.
iRemove from the milk, peel away the skin, then flake the flesh into thumbsize pieces.
iPlace the eggs in a pan, cover with water, bring to the boil, then reduce to a simmer.
iLeave for 4½-5 mins, plunge into cold water, then peel and cut the eggs into quarters.
iGently mix the fish, eggs, parsley, coriander and rice together in the pan.
iServe hot, sprinkled with a few extra herbs.
