nPortuguese fish stew (Caldeirada de peixe)
cSeafood
d53045
iHeat a drizzle of oil in a large, deep-sided frying pan, and fry the onion and pepper on a medium heat until softened but not browned.
iFinely chop the coriander stalks (keep the leaves for later), and add to the pan with the chilli and chopped garlic.
iFry for another few minutes.
iAdd the wine, saffron and bay leaf and let it simmer until reduced by half.
iAdd the potatoes, tomatoes, and 300ml water and bring to a gentle boil.
iBreak up the tomatoes with a spoon on the side of the pan and simmer for 20-25 minutes until the potatoes are just tender, and the tomatoes have broken down.
iSeason well, then gently push the fish into the sauce, and arrange the squid, prawns, clams and mussels on the surface.
iPut the lid on and cook for 6-8 minutes until the mussel and clam shells have opened, the prawns are cooked and the fish is flaky.
iToast the bread, rub lightly with the halved garlic clove and drizzle with olive oil.
iServe the stew scatted with chopped coriander leaves, and the toasts for dunking.
