nRecheado Masala Fish
cSeafood
d52809
iSoak all the spices, ginger, garlic, tamarind pulp and kashmiri chilies except oil in vinegar.
iAdd sugar and salt.
iAlso add turmeric powder.
iCombine all nicely and marinate for 35-40 mins.
iGrind the mixture until soft and smooth.
iAdd more vinegar if required but ensure the paste has to be thick so add vinegar accordingly.
iIf the masala paste is thin then it would not stick to the fish.
iRinse the fish slit from the center and give some incision from the top.
iYou could see the fish below for clarity.
iNow stuff the paste into the center and into the incision.
iCoat the entire fish with this paste.
iMarinate the fish for 30 mins.
iPlace oil in a shallow pan, once oil is quite hot shallow fry the stuffed mackerels.
iServe the recheado mackerels hot with salad, lime wedges, rice and curry.
i1. Ensure the masala paste is thick else the result won't be good.
i2. If you aren't able to find kashmiri chilies then use bedgi chilies or kashmiri red chili powder.
i3. You could use white vinegar or coconut vinegar.
i4. Any left over paste could be stored in the fridge for future use.
i5. Cinnamon could be avoided as it's a strong spice used generally for meat or chicken.
