nSaltfish and Ackee
cSeafood
d52936
iFor the saltfish, soak the salt cod overnight, changing the water a couple of times.
iDrain, then put the cod in a large pan of fresh water and bring to the boil.
iDrain again, add fresh water and bring to the boil again.
iSimmer for about five minutes, or until cooked through, then drain and flake the fish into large pieces.
iDiscard any skin or bones.
iFor the dumplings, mix the flour and suet with a pinch of salt and 250ml/9fl oz water to make a dough.
iWrap the mixture in clingfilm and leave in the fridge to rest.
iOpen the can of ackee, drain and rinse, then set aside.
iHeat a tablespoon of olive oil in a pan and fry the onion until softened but not brown.
iAdd the spices, seasoning, pepper sauce and sliced peppers and continue to fry until the peppers are tender.
iAdd the chopped tomatoes, then the salt cod and mix together.
iLastly stir in the ackee very gently and leave to simmer until ready to serve.
iWhen you’re almost ready to eat, heat about 1cm/½in vegetable oil in a frying pan and heat until just smoking.
iShape the dumpling mix into plum-size balls and shallow-fry until golden-brown.
i(CAUTION: hot oil can be dangerous.
iDo not leave the pan unattended.
iDrain the dumplings on kitchen paper and serve with the saltfish and ackee.
