nSeafood fideuà
cSeafood
d52836
iBoil the kettle.
iEmpty the mussels into a colander and run under cold water.
iThrow away any with broken shells.
iPick through the shells, tapping each one on the side of the sink – they should be closed or should slowly close when tapped – if they stay open, throw them away.
iIf any of the shells still have barnacles or stringy beards attached, pull them off with a cutlery knife and rinse the shells well.
iKeep in the colander, covered with a cold, damp cloth, until you’re ready to cook.
iPeel the prawn shells on the body section only – leave the heads and tails intact.
iScore down the backs and pull out any gritty entrails.
iChill until you’re ready to cook.
iPut the saffron in a small cup, cover with 50ml kettle-hot water and set aside for 10 mins.
iIf using vermicelli, put in a bowl and crush to little pieces (about 1cm long) with your hands.
iHeat the oil in a large frying pan with at least a 3cm lip, or a 40cm paella pan.
iAdd the onion and stir around the pan for 5 mins until soft.
iAdd the garlic and cook for 1 min more, then tip in the vermicelli and cook for 5 mins, stirring from time to time, until the vermicelli is toasted brown.
iStir in the paprika.
iKeeping the heat moderate, stir through the monkfish, squid and saffron with its water, seasoning well.
iSpread the ingredients out in an even layer, then pour over the hot stock and scatter the tomatoes on top.
iBring to a simmer, then cover the whole dish with a tight-fitting lid (or foil).
iTurn the heat to medium and cook for 6 mins.
iUncover and stir to incorporate the dry top layer of pasta.
iPush the mussels into the pasta so the hinges are buried in the bottom of the dish, and they stand straight up.
iArrange the prawns on top, cover tightly and cook for another 6 mins or until the mussels are open, the prawns are pink and the pasta is cooked through.
iLeave to simmer for another 2-3 mins to cook off most of the remaining liquid (leave a little in the pan to prevent the pasta from sticking together).
iAllow to sit for 2-3 mins, then squeeze over the lemon juice and arrange the wedges on top.
iScatter with parsley before serving.
