nThree Fish Pie
cSeafood
d52882
iPreheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6 (180C fan).
iPut the potatoes into a saucepan of cold salted water.
iBring up to the boil and simmer until completely tender.
iDrain well and then mash with the butter and milk.
iAdd pepper and taste to check the seasoning.
iAdd salt and more pepper if necessary.
iFor the fish filling, melt the butter in a saucepan, add the leeks and stir over the heat.
iCover with a lid and simmer gently for 10 minutes, or until soft.
iMeasure the flour into a small bowl.
iAdd the wine and whisk together until smooth.
iAdd the milk to the leeks, bring to the boil and then add the wine mixture.
iStir briskly until thickened.
iSeason and add the parsley and fish.
iStir over the heat for two minutes, then spoon into an ovenproof casserole.
iScatter over the eggs.
iAllow to cool until firm.
iSpoon the mashed potatoes over the fish mixture and mark with a fork.
iSprinkle with cheese.
iBake for 30-40 minutes, or until lightly golden-brown on top and bubbling around the edges.
