nTuna Nicoise
cSeafood
d52852
iHeat oven to 200C/fan 180C/gas 6.
iToss the potatoes with 2 tsp oil and some seasoning.
iTip onto a large baking tray, then roast for 20 mins, stirring halfway, until crisp, golden and cooked through.
iMeanwhile, put eggs in a small pan of water, bring to the boil, then simmer for 8-10 mins, depending on how you like them cooked.
iPlunge into a bowl of cold water to cool for a few mins.
iPeel away the shells, then cut into halves.
iIn a large salad bowl, whisk together the remaining oil, red wine vinegar, capers and chopped tomatoes.
iSeason, tip in the onion, spinach, tuna and potatoes, then gently toss together.
iTop with the eggs, then serve straight away.
