nBrie wrapped in prosciutto & brioche
cSide
d52913
iMix the flour, 1 tsp salt, caster sugar, yeast, milk and eggs together in a mixer using the dough attachment for 5 mins until the dough is smooth.
iAdd the butter and mix for a further 4 mins on medium speed.
iScrape the dough bowl and mix again for 1 min.
iPlace the dough in a container, cover with cling film and leave in the fridge for at least 6 hrs before using.
iWrap the Brie in the prosciutto and set aside.
iTurn out the dough onto a lightly floured surface.
iRoll into a 25cm circle.
iPlace the wrapped Brie in the middle of the circle and fold the edges in neatly.
iPut the parcel onto a baking tray lined with baking parchment and brush with beaten egg.
iChill in the fridge for 30 mins, then brush again with beaten egg and chill for a further 30 mins.
iLeave to rise for 1 hr at room temperature.
iHeat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6, then bake for 22 mins.
iServe warm.
