nFeteer Meshaltet
cSide
d53030
iMix the flour and salt then pour one cup of water and start kneading.
iIf you feel the dough is still not coming together or too dry, gradually add the remaining water until you get a dough that is very elastic so that when you pull it and it won’t be torn.
iLet the dough rest for just 10 minutes then divide the dough into 6-8 balls depending on the size you want for your feteer.
iWarm up the butter/ghee or oil you are using and pour into a deep bowl.
iImmerse the dough balls into the warm butter.
iLet it rest for 15 to 20 minutes.
iPreheat oven to 550F.
iStretch the first ball with your hands on a clean countertop.
iStretch it as thin as you can, the goal here is to see your countertop through the dough.
iFold the dough over itself to form a square brushing in between folds with the butter mixture.
iSet aside and start making the next ball.
iStretch the second one thin as we have done for the first ball.
iPlace the previous one on the middle seam side down.
iFold the outer one over brushing with more butter mixture as you fold.
iSet aside.
iKeep doing this for the third and fourth balls.
iNow we have one ready, place on a 10 inch baking/pie dish seam side down and brush the top with more butter.
iRepeat for the remaining 4 balls to make a second one.
iWith your hands lightly press the folded feteer to spread it on the baking dish.
iPlace in preheated oven for 10 minutes when the feteer starts puffing turn on the broiler to brown the top.
iWhen it is done add little butter on top and cover so it won’t get dry.
