nFrench Onion Soup
cSide
d52903
iMelt the butter with the oil in a large heavy-based pan.
iAdd the onions and fry with the lid on for 10 mins until soft.
iSprinkle in the sugar and cook for 20 mins more, stirring frequently, until caramelised.
iThe onions should be really golden, full of flavour and soft when pinched between your fingers.
iTake care towards the end to ensure that they don’t burn.
iAdd the garlic for the final few mins of the onions’ cooking time, then sprinkle in the flour and stir well.
iIncrease the heat and keep stirring as you gradually add the wine, followed by the hot stock.
iCover and simmer for 15-20 mins.
iTo serve, turn on the grill, and toast the bread.
iLadle the soup into heatproof bowls.
iPut a slice or two of toast on top of the bowls of soup, and pile on the cheese.
iGrill until melted.
iAlternatively, you can complete the toasts under the grill, then serve them on top.
