nPierogi (Polish Dumplings)
cSide
d53019
iTo prepare the sauerkraut filling, melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
iStir in the onion, and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.
iAdd the drained sauerkraut and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
iSeason to taste with salt and pepper, then remove to a plate to cool.
iFor the mashed potato filling, melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
iStir in the onion, and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.
iStir into the mashed potatoes, and season with salt and white pepper.
iTo make the dough, beat together the eggs and sour cream until smooth.
iSift together the flour, salt, and baking powder; stir into the sour cream mixture until dough comes together.
iKnead the dough on a lightly floured surface until firm and smooth.
iDivide the dough in half, then roll out one half to 1/8 inch thickness.
iCut into 3 inch rounds using a biscuit cutter.
iPlace a small spoonful of the mashed potato filling into the center of each round.
iMoisten the edges with water, fold over, and press together with a fork to seal.
iRepeat procedure with the remaining dough and the sauerkraut filling.
iBring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
iAdd perogies and cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until pierogi float to the top.
iRemove with a slotted spoon.
