nPrawn & Fennel Bisque
cSide
d52922
iShell the prawns, then fry the shells in the oil in a large pan for about 5 mins.
iAdd the onion, fennel and carrots and cook for about 10 mins until the veg start to soften.
iPour in the wine and brandy, bubble hard for about 1 min to drive off the alcohol, then add the tomatoes, stock and paprika.
iCover and simmer for 30 mins.
iMeanwhile, chop the prawns.
iBlitz the soup as finely as you can with a stick blender or food processor, then press through a sieve into a bowl.
iSpend a bit of time really working the mixture through the sieve as this will give the soup its velvety texture.
iTip back into a clean pan, add the prawns and cook for 10 mins, then blitz again until smooth.
iYou can make and chill this a day ahead or freeze it for 1 month.
iThaw ovenight in the fridge.
iTo serve, gently reheat in a pan with the cream.
iIf garnishing, cook the 8 prawns in a little butter.
iSpoon into small bowls and top with the prawns and snipped fennel fronds.
