nSnert (Dutch Split Pea Soup)
cSide
d52981
iGather the ingredients.
iIn a large soup pot, bring water, split peas, pork belly or bacon, pork chop, and bouillon cube to a boil.
iReduce the heat to a simmer, cover and let cook for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally and skimming off any foam that rises to the top.
iRemove the pork chop, debone, and thinly slice the meat.
iSet aside.
iAdd the celery, carrots, potato, onion, leek, and celeriac to the soup.
iReturn to the boil, reduce the heat to a simmer and let cook, uncovered, for another 30 minutes, adding a little extra water if the ingredients start to stick to the bottom of the pot.
iAdd the smoked sausage for the last 15 minutes of cooking time.
iWhen the vegetables are tender, remove the bacon and smoked sausage, slice thinly and set aside.
iIf you prefer a smooth consistency, purée the soup with a stick blender.
iSeason to taste with salt and pepper.
iAdd the meat back to the soup, setting some slices of rookworst aside.
iServe in heated bowls or soup plates, garnished with slices of rookworst and chopped celery leaf.
