nSplit Pea Soup
cSide
d52925
iPut the gammon in a very large pan with 2 litres water and bring to the boil.
iRemove from the heat and drain off the water – this helps to get rid of some of the saltiness.
iRecover with 2 litres cold water and bring to the boil again.
iPut everything but the frozen peas into the pan and bring to the boil.
iReduce to a simmer and cook for 1½-2½ hrs, topping up the water as and when you need to, to a similar level it started at.
iAs the ham cooks and softens, you can halve it if you want, so it is all submerged under the liquid.
iWhen the ham is tender enough to pull into shreds, it is ready.
iLift out the ham, peel off and discard the skin.
iWhile it is still hot (wear a clean pair of rubber gloves), shred the meat.
iRemove bay from the soup and stir in the frozen peas.
iSimmer for 1 min, then blend until smooth.
iAdd a splash of water if too thick, and return to the pan to heat through if it has cooled, or if you are making ahead.
iWhen you are ready to serve, mix the hot soup with most of the ham – gently reheat if made ahead.
iServe in bowls with the remaining ham scattered on top, and eat with crusty bread and butter.
