nBroccoli & Stilton soup
cStarter
d52842
iHeat the rapeseed oil in a large saucepan and then add the onions.
iCook on a medium heat until soft.
iAdd a splash of water if the onions start to catch.
iAdd the celery, leek, potato and a knob of butter.
iStir until melted, then cover with a lid.
iAllow to sweat for 5 minutes.
iRemove the lid.
iPour in the stock and add any chunky bits of broccoli stalk.
iCook for 10 – 15 minutes until all the vegetables are soft.
iAdd the rest of the broccoli and cook for a further 5 minutes.
iCarefully transfer to a blender and blitz until smooth.
iStir in the stilton, allowing a few lumps to remain.
iSeason with black pepper and serve.
