nClam chowder
cStarter
d52840
iRinse the clams in several changes of cold water and drain well.
iTip the clams into a large pan with 500ml of water.
iCover, bring to the boil and simmer for 2 mins until the clams have just opened.
iTip the contents of the pan into a colander over a bowl to catch the clam stock.
iWhen cool enough to handle, remove the clams from their shells – reserving a handful of empty shells for presentation if you want.
iStrain the clam stock into a jug, leaving any grit in the bottom of the bowl.
iYou should have around 800ml stock.
iHeat the butter in the same pan and sizzle the bacon for 3-4 mins until it starts to brown.
iStir in the onion, thyme and bay and cook everything gently for 10 mins until the onion is soft and golden.
iScatter over the flour and stir in to make a sandy paste, cook for 2 mins more, then gradually stir in the clam stock then the milk and the cream.
iThrow in the potatoes, bring everything to a simmer and leave to bubble away gently for 10 mins or until the potatoes are cooked.
iUse a fork to crush a few of the potato chunks against the side of the pan to help thicken – you still want lots of defined chunks though.
iStir through the clam meat and the few clam shells, if you've gone down that route, and simmer for a minute to reheat.
iSeason with plenty of black pepper and a little salt, if needed, then stir through the parsley just before ladling into bowls or hollowed-out crusty rolls.
