i6. Peel the skin from the roasted and smoked eggplant.
i7. Chop the cooked eggplant finely or you can even mash it.
i8. In a kadai or pan, heat oil.
iThen add finely chopped onions and garlic.
i9. Saute the onions till translucent.
iDon't brown them.
i10.
iAdd chopped green chilies and saute for a minute.
i11.
iAdd the chopped tomatoes and mix it well.
i12.
iBhuno (saute) the tomatoes till the oil starts separating from the mixture.
i13.
iNow add the red chili powder.
iStir and mix well.
i14.
iAdd the chopped cooked baingan.
i15.
iStir and mix the chopped baingan very well with the onion­tomato masala mixture.
i16.
iSeason with salt.
iStir and saute for some more 4 to 5 minutes more.
i17.
iFinally stir in the coriander leaves with the baingan bharta or garnish it with them.
iphulkas, rotis or chapatis.
iIt goes well even with bread, toasted or grilled bread and plain rice or jeera rice.
