nGigantes Plaki
cVegetarian
d53012
iSoak the beans overnight in plenty of water.
iDrain, rinse, then place in a pan covered with water.
iBring to the boil, reduce the heat, then simmer for approx 50 mins until slightly tender but not soft.
iDrain, then set aside.
iHeat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4.
iHeat the olive oil in a large frying pan, tip in the onion and garlic, then cook over a medium heat for 10 mins until softened but not browned.
iAdd the tomato purée, cook for a further min, add remaining ingredients, then simmer for 2-3 mins.
iSeason generously, then stir in the beans.
iTip into a large ovenproof dish, then bake for approximately 1 hr, uncovered and without stirring, until the beans are tender.
iThe beans will absorb all the fabulous flavours and the sauce will thicken.
iAllow to cool, then scatter with parsley and drizzle with a little more olive oil to serve.
