nKafteji
cVegetarian
d52971
iPeel potatoes and cut into 5cm cubes.
iPour 1-2 cm of olive oil into a large pan and heat up very hot.
iFry potatoes until golden brown for 20 minutes, turning from time to time.
iPlace on kitchen paper to drain.
iCut the peppers in half and remove seeds.
iRub a little olive oil on them and place the cut side down on a baking tray.
iPlace them under the grill.
iGrill until the skin is dark and bubbly.
iWhile the peppers are still hot, put them into a plastic sandwich bag and seal it.
iTake them out after 15 minutes and remove skins.
iIn the meantime, heat more olive oil another pan.
iPeel the onions and cut into thin rings.
iFry for 15 minutes until golden brown, turning them often.
iAdd the Ras el hanout at the end.
iCut the pumpkin into 5cm cubes and fry in the same pan you used for the potatoes for 10-15 minutes until it is soft and slightly browned.
iPlace on kitchen paper.
iPour the remaining olive oil out of the pan and put all the cooked vegetables into the pan and mix.
iWhisk eggs and pour them over the vegetables.
iPut the lid on the pan so that the eggs cook.
iPut the contents of the pan onto a large chopping board, add salt and pepper and chopped and mix everything with a big knife.
