nKidney Bean Curry
cVegetarian
d52868
iHeat the oil in a large frying pan over a low-medium heat.
iAdd the onion and a pinch of salt and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until softened and just starting to colour.
iAdd the garlic, ginger and coriander stalks and cook for a further 2 mins, until fragrant.
iAdd the spices to the pan and cook for another 1 min, by which point everything should smell aromatic.
iTip in the chopped tomatoes and kidney beans in their water, then bring to the boil.
iTurn down the heat and simmer for 15 mins until the curry is nice and thick.
