nRatatouille
cVegetarian
d52908
iCut the aubergines in half lengthways.
iPlace them on the board, cut side down, slice in half lengthways again and then across into 1.
i5cm chunks.
iCut off the courgettes ends, then across into 1.
i5cm slices.
iPeel the peppers from stalk to bottom.
iHold upright, cut around the stalk, then cut into 3 pieces.
iCut away any membrane, then chop into bite-size chunks.
iScore a small cross on the base of each tomato, then put them into a heatproof bowl.
iPour boiling water over the tomatoes, leave for 20 secs, then remove.
iPour the water away, replace the tomatoes and cover with cold water.
iLeave to cool, then peel the skin away.
iQuarter the tomatoes, scrape away the seeds with a spoon, then roughly chop the flesh.
iSet a sauté pan over medium heat and when hot, pour in 2 tbsp olive oil.
iBrown the aubergines for 5 mins on each side until the pieces are soft.
iSet them aside and fry the courgettes in another tbsp oil for 5 mins, until golden on both sides.
iRepeat with the peppers.
iDon’t overcook the vegetables at this stage, as they have some more cooking left in the next step.
iTear up the basil leaves and set aside.
iCook the onion in the pan for 5 mins.
iAdd the garlic and fry for a further min.
iStir in the vinegar and sugar, then tip in the tomatoes and half the basil.
iReturn the vegetables to the pan with some salt and pepper and cook for 5 mins.
iServe with basil.
