nRibollita
cVegetarian
d52811
iPut 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large pot over medium heat.
iWhen it’s hot, add onion, carrot, celery and garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft, 5 to 10 minutes.
iHeat the oven to 500 degrees.
iDrain the beans; if they’re canned, rinse them as well.
iAdd them to the pot along with tomatoes and their juices and stock, rosemary and thyme.
iBring to a boil, then reduce heat so the soup bubbles steadily; cover and cook, stirring once or twice to break up the tomatoes, until the flavors meld, 15 to 20 minutes.
