nSpinach & Ricotta Cannelloni
cVegetarian
d52849
iFirst make the tomato sauce.
iHeat the oil in a large pan and fry the garlic for 1 min.
iAdd the sugar, vinegar, tomatoes and some seasoning and simmer for 20 mins, stirring occasionally, until thick.
iAdd the basil and divide the sauce between 2 or more shallow ovenproof dishes (see Tips for freezing, below).
iSet aside.
iMake a sauce by beating the mascarpone with the milk until smooth, season, then set aside.
iPut the spinach in a large colander and pour over a kettle of boiling water to wilt it (you may need to do this in batches).
iWhen cool enough to handle squeeze out the excess water.
iRoughly chop the spinach and mix in a large bowl with 100g Parmesan and ricotta.
iSeason well with salt, pepper and the nutmeg.
iHeat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6.
iUsing a piping bag or plastic food bag with the corner snipped off, squeeze the filling into the cannelloni tubes.
iLay the tubes, side by side, on top of the tomato sauce and spoon over the mascarpone sauce.
iTop with Parmesan and mozzarella.
iYou can now freeze the cannelloni, uncooked, or you can cook it first and then freeze.
iBake for 30-35 mins until golden and bubbling.
iRemove from oven and let stand for 5 mins before serving.
