nTamiya
cVegetarian
d53026
ioak the beans in water to cover overnight.
iDrain.
iIf skinless beans are unavailable, rub to loosen the skins, then discard the skins.
iPat the beans dry with a towel.
iGrind the beans in a food mill or meat grinder.
iIf neither appliance is available, process them in a food processor but only until the beans form a paste.
i(If blended too smoothly, the batter tends to fall apart during cooking.
i) Add the scallions, garlic, cilantro, cumin, baking powder, cayenne, salt, pepper, and coriander, if using.
iRefrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
iShape the bean mixture into 1-inch balls.
iFlatten slightly and coat with flour.
iHeat at least 1½-inches of oil over medium heat to 365 degrees.
iFry the patties in batches, turning once, until golden brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.
iRemove with a wire mesh skimmer or slotted spoon.
iServe as part of a meze or in pita bread with tomato-cucumber salad and tahina sauce.
