nBreakfast Potatoes
cBreakfast
d52965
iWash the potatoes and cut medium dice into square pieces.
iTo prevent any browning, place the already cut potatoes in a bowl filled with water.
iIn the meantime, heat 1-2 tablespoons of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
iTilt the skillet so the oil spreads evenly.
iOnce the oil is hot, drain the potatoes and add to the skillet.
iSeason with salt, pepper, and Old Bay as needed.
iCook for 10 minutes, stirring the potatoes often, until brown.
iIf needed, add a tablespoon more of oil.
iChop up the bacon and add to the potatoes.
iThe bacon will start to render and the fat will begin to further cook the potatoes.
iToss it up a bit! The bacon will take 5-6 minutes to crisp.
iOnce the bacon is cooked, reduce the heat to medium-low, add the minced garlic and toss.
iSeason once more.
iAdd dried or fresh parsley.
iControl heat as needed.
iLet the garlic cook until fragrant, about one minute.
iJust before serving, drizzle over the maple syrup and toss.
iLet that cook another minute, giving the potatoes a caramelized effect.
