nEnglish Breakfast
cBreakfast
d52895
iHeat the flat grill plate over a low heat, on top of 2 rings/flames if it fits, and brush sparingly with light olive oil.
iCook the sausages first.
iAdd the sausages to the hot grill plate/the coolest part if there is one and allow to cook slowly for about 15-20 minutes, turning occasionally, until golden.
iAfter the first 10 minutes, increase the heat to medium before beginning to cook the other ingredients.
iIf you are struggling for space, completely cook the sausages and keep hot on a plate in the oven.
iSnip a few small cuts into the fatty edge of the bacon.
iPlace the bacon straight on to the grill plate and fry for 2-4 minutes each side or until your preferred crispiness is reached.
iLike the sausages, the cooked bacon can be kept hot on a plate in the oven.
iFor the mushrooms, brush away any dirt using a pastry brush and trim the stalk level with the mushroom top.
iSeason with salt and pepper and drizzle over a little olive oil.
iPlace stalk-side up on the grill plate and cook for 1-2 minutes before turning and cooking for a further 3-4 minutes.
iAvoid moving the mushrooms too much while cooking, as this releases the natural juices, making them soggy.
iFor the tomatoes, cut the tomatoes across the centre/or in half lengthways if using plum tomatoes , and with a small, sharp knife remove the green 'eye'.
iSeason with salt and pepper and drizzle with a little olive oil.
iPlace cut-side down on the grill plate and cook without moving for 2 minutes.
iGently turn over and season again.
iCook for a further 2-3 minutes until tender but still holding their shape.
iFor the black pudding, cut the black pudding into 3-4 slices and remove the skin.
iPlace on the grill plate and cook for 1½-2 minutes each side until slightly crispy.
iFor 'proper' fried bread it's best to cook it in a separate pan.
iIdeally, use bread that is a couple of days old.
iHeat a frying pan to a medium heat and cover the base with oil.
iAdd the bread and cook for 2-3 minutes each side until crispy and golden.
iIf the pan becomes too dry, add a little more oil.
iFor a richer flavour, add a knob of butter after you turn the slice.
iFor the fried eggs, break the egg straight into the pan with the fried bread and leave for 30 seconds.
iAdd a good knob of butter and lightly splash/baste the egg with the butter when melted.
iCook to your preferred stage, season and gently remove with a fish slice.
iOnce all the ingredients are cooked, serve on warm plates and enjoy straight away with a good squeeze of tomato ketchup or brown sauce.
