nFruit and Cream Cheese Breakfast Pastries
cBreakfast
d52957
iPreheat oven to 400ºF (200ºC), and prepare two cookie sheets with parchment paper.
iIn a bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla until fully combined.
iLightly flour the surface and roll out puff pastry on top to flatten.
iCut each sheet of puff pastry into 9 equal squares.
iOn the top right and bottom left of the pastry, cut an L shape approximately ½ inch (1 cm) from the edge.
iNOTE: This L shape should reach all the way down and across the square, however both L shapes should not meet at the ends.
iYour pastry should look like a picture frame with two corners still intact.
iTake the upper right corner and fold down towards the inner bottom corner.
iYou will now have a diamond shape.
iPlace 1 to 2 teaspoons of the cream cheese filling in the middle, then place berries on top.
iRepeat with the remaining pastry squares and place them onto the parchment covered baking sheet.
iBake for 15-20 minutes or until pastry is golden brown and puffed.
