cBreakfast
d52962
iFirst make the Hollandaise sauce.
iPut the lemon juice and vinegar in a small bowl, add the egg yolks and whisk with a balloon whisk until light and frothy.
iPlace the bowl over a pan of simmering water and whisk until mixture thickens.
iGradually add the butter, whisking constantly until thick – if it looks like it might be splitting, then whisk off the heat for a few mins.
iSeason and keep warm.
iTo poach the eggs, bring a large pan of water to the boil and add the vinegar.
iLower the heat so that the water is simmering gently.
iStir the water so you have a slight whirlpool, then slide in the eggs one by one.
iCook each for about 4 mins, then remove with a slotted spoon.
iLightly toast and butter the muffins, then put a couple of slices of salmon on each half.
iTop each with an egg, spoon over some Hollandaise and garnish with chopped chives.
