nSmoked Haddock Kedgeree
cBreakfast
d52964
iMelt 50g butter in a large saucepan (about 20cm across), add 1 finely chopped medium onion and cook gently over a medium heat for 5 minutes, until softened but not browned.
iStir in 3 split cardamom pods, ¼ tsp turmeric, 1 small cinnamon stick and 2 bay leaves, then cook for 1 minute.
iTip in 450g basmati rice and stir until it is all well coated in the spicy butter.
iPour in 1 litre chicken or fish stock, add ½ teaspoon salt and bring to the boil, stir once to release any rice from the bottom of the pan.
iCover with a close-fitting lid, reduce the heat to low and leave to cook very gently for 12 minutes.
iMeanwhile, bring some water to the boil in a large shallow pan.
iAdd 750g un-dyed smoked haddock fillet and simmer for 4 minutes, until the fish is just cooked.
iLift it out onto a plate and leave until cool enough to handle.
iHard-boil 3 eggs for 8 minutes.
iFlake the fish, discarding any skin and bones.
iDrain the eggs, cool slightly, then peel and chop.
iUncover the rice and remove the bay leaves, cinnamon stick and cardamom pods if you wish to.
iGently fork in the fish and the chopped eggs, cover again and return to the heat for 2-3 minutes, or until the fish has heated through.
iGently stir in almost all the 3 tbsp chopped fresh parsley, and season with a little salt and black pepper to taste.
iServe scattered with the remaining parsley and garnished with 1 lemon, cut into wedges.
