cGoat
d52968
iRoast meat over medium heat for 50 minutes and salt it as you turn it.
iBring the water and salt to a boil in a heavy-bottomed saucepan.
iStir in the cornmeal slowly, letting it fall through the fingers of your hand.
i3. Reduce heat to medium-low and continue stirring regularly, smashing any lumps with a spoon, until the mush pulls away from the sides of the pot and becomes very thick, about 10 minutes.
i4.Remove from heat and allow to cool.
i5. Place the ugali into a large serving bowl.
iWet your hands with water, form a ball and serve.
i6. Steps for Kachumbari: Mix the tomatoes, onions, chili and coriander leaves in a bowl.
